ad_creative_body:
Every one of the Democratic candidates remaining would make a better president than Donald Trump. But the race for the Democratic nomination is a fractured one. It's not a straightforward narrative captured by glancing at a map, and the process won't be decided by the simple horse race numbers in clickbait headlines. That's never been our focus — our focus is on building a broad coalition to win delegates everywhere.

For months, Elizabeth has been near or at the top of the list of candidates that voters are considering for president. According to the latest Economist/YouGov poll, 40-50% of voters across all age groups are considering voting for Warren, including 58% of self-described liberals and 38% of self-described moderates. Elizabeth is best positioned to unite the party and lead the Democratic ticket to defeat Donald Trump.

Our campaign is no stranger to being written off or counted out early. But here's what we do know: Elizabeth has proven the doubters wrong before.

Elizabeth is progressive, effective, and has lived a life that has prepared her for this fight. With a strong organization of more than 1,000 staff on the ground in 31 states, bolstered by a movement of more than 1,000,000 grassroots donors, we are confident that as Americans continue to get to know Elizabeth, they'll see what we see every day: Elizabeth is the only candidate who can unite the party and defeat Donald Trump in November. 

But the only way we'll win this nomination is if everyone reading this digs deep and funds our 100% grassroots-funded campaign. Can you help us keep moving forward? Chip in $2, $20 or whatever you can to power this movement through the critical races to come.
label: Foreign policy,Governance,Social Programs

Then she said that she still chipped in $3 to our campaign that night. Because that was how important this campaign was to her. 

I’m not done fighting for working people, for students, for anybody who believes that we can make things better than they are now. Our campaign is 100% grassroots funded, and we need everyone to dig in deep and chip in $3, $20, or whatever they can today to help us keep moving forward. Can I count on you?

Una cosa queda clara: ahorrar para una jubilación decente se está volviendo más difícil y el programa del Seguro Social se ha convertido la fuente principal de ingreso para muchos de nosotros que tenemos más de 65 años.

Elizabeth ha ayudado a liderar la lucha en el Congreso para ampliar el programa del Seguro Social y su plan proporcionaría el mayor aumento a los beneficios del Seguro Social en casi medio siglo. Si estás de acuerdo que necesitamos aumentar los beneficios del Seguro Social por $200 al mes y actualizar la reglas, inscríbete hoy para unirte a Elizabeth.

***

One thing is clear: it’s getting harder to save enough for a decent retirement and Social Security has become a main source of income for many of us who are over 65.

Elizabeth has helped lead the fight in Congress to expand Social Security, and her plan would provide the biggest and most progressive increase in Social Security benefits in nearly half a century. If you agree that we need to increase Social Security benefits by $200 a month and update its rules, sign up to join Elizabeth today.
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_body:
“‘I think it is really important that as we go into the 2020 election that we have the best chance to win against Donald Trump,’ Warren said. ‘And I think what that’s going to be is about prosecuting the case on corruption and drawing the distinction between this administration that is the most corrupt in living memory, and having a Democratic nominee who was willing to take on that corruption.’”

“‘We win when we have ideas big enough to meet the problems in people’s lives.’”
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Unpredictable work schedules leave millions of part-time workers with no control over their time. My Fair Workweek plan gives these workers more control and financial security.
ad_creative_link_title: A Fair Work Week for America’s Part-Time Workers
ad_creative_body:
As I travel the country talking to workers at town halls and in selfie lines, I hear that too many face a giant challenge in supporting their families: unpredictable work schedules that leave them with too few hours to afford necessities and no control over their time. 

Across the country, workers are fed up with unpredictable and unfair schedules so they’re getting organized - and winning.

My Fair Workweek plan builds on the work of these committed advocates and activists, and ensures that every part-time worker in America is treated with respect and can build a future for themselves and the people they love. It will: 
- Require employers with 15 or more employees to give two weeks of advance notice of work schedules
- Empower employees to ask for schedules that work for them without fear of retaliation.
- Ensure a right to rest between shifts.
- Require employers to offer additional work hours to existing, qualified, part-time workers before hiring new employees or contractors.
- Provide benefits to part-time workers.

Click here to read more.
label: Economic,Governance

Desert Pines High School, Cafeteria
3800 E Harris Ave
Las Vegas, NV 89110

WHEN:
Saturday, February 15
Doors at 9:30 AM 
Event at 10:30 AM

Our Future, Our Fight.

ad_creative_body: We WON New Hampshire! Our job now is to make this one of our biggest fundraising days yet, and send an unmistakable message to the establishment that we intend to keep winning – next in Nevada, then in this primary, and then against Donald Trump. Can we count on you to make a contribution to stand with us?
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Learn How and Where to Vote for Bernie
ad_creative_body: As a Nevadan, the most important thing you can do for Bernie is to vote early for Bernie between February 15th and 18th, or caucus for Bernie on February 22nd. Click below to find out how and where to caucus, then come out and help us elect Bernie and make history.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Your support sends a powerful message to the economic and political establishment.
ad_creative_link_title: Sign Up to Caucus for Bernie
ad_creative_body: We’re not just taking on Donald Trump or our democratic opponents. We’re taking on the entire political establishment. But we know we can win, because we are building an unprecedented grassroots movement of millions of people. Join us and sign up to caucus with us.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Your support sends a powerful message to the economic and political establishment.
ad_creative_link_title: Sign Up to Caucus for Bernie
ad_creative_body:
I’ve got a small favor to ask – please add your name to say you will caucus with our campaign. We are taking on the most powerful forces in this country, and they have unbelievable and unlimited amounts of money to spend against us. 

But we’ve got something even better: you. Add your name to show them we’re ready to take them on and win.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Your support sends a powerful message to the economic and political establishment.
ad_creative_link_title: Sign Up to Caucus for Bernie
ad_creative_body: I’ve got a small favor to ask – can you add your name to endorse our campaign?
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: Your support sends a powerful message to the economic and political establishment.
ad_creative_link_title: Sign Up to Caucus for Bernie
ad_creative_body: Can you add your name to show you will caucus with our campaign? Every person we can show is on our side helps us prove to the political and economic establishment just how powerful we are.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Your support sends a powerful message to the economic and political establishment.
ad_creative_link_title: Sign Up to Caucus for Bernie
ad_creative_body:
Our campaign is taking on Wall Street, the insurance companies, the drug companies, the military-industrial complex, the prison-industrial complex, the fossil fuel industry and a corrupt campaign finance system that enables billionaires to buy elections.

No candidate can take them on alone. There is only one way, and that is by building a movement strong enough to beat them. Will you join us by adding your name?
label: Economic,Environment,Governance,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: As president, Tom will establish a formal commission on reparations to figure out the best way to right the wrongs of the past. If you're with him, join our campaign today.
ad_creative_link_title: I'm not afraid to call for reparations
ad_creative_body: I'm fiercely committed to working with communities of color to make their voices heard in Washington. As president, I'll establish a formal commission on reparations to right the wrongs of the past directly. If you're with us, join our campaign.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_title: We must work together on climate
ad_creative_body: We can't talk about foreign policy without talking about climate change. Instead of spending billions waging endless wars, we need to focus on building relationships with allies so we can solve the climate crisis together. Join our campaign to reinstate America as the global leader on climate.
label: Environment,Foreign policy

ad_creative_link_description: We asked Tom Steyer 20 questions on subjects that include debating President Trump, economic priorities and celebrity crushes.
ad_creative_link_title: My thoughts on today's biggest questions
ad_creative_body: How will I drive action on the climate crisis? I'll declare a national climate emergency on day one and enact a climate plan that gets us to zero emissions by 2040. The climate crisis can't wait. See more of my answers to some of the biggest questions facing our nation below.
label: Environment

ad_creative_link_title: We’ll end Trump’s war on immigrants
ad_creative_body: As president, I’ll end Trump’s war on nonwhite immigrants. He has broken the laws of humanity in our name. When it comes to immigration policy, we have to start with the idea that immigrants are full human beings whose rights must be respected.
label: Immigration

ad_creative_link_description: Will you commit to vote or caucus for Tom in your state?
ad_creative_link_title: NV: Will you commit to Tom?
ad_creative_body: Tom believes the economy should work for everyone, not just the rich. That's why his tax plan grants a 10% tax cut to 95% of Americans by ending giveaways and tax breaks for the wealthy. Will you commit to caucus for Tom so he can make his plan a reality?
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_body: Juntos podemos restaurar nuestra democracia para que vuelva a ser de, por, y para el pueblo. ¡Únete a nuestra campaña! #TodosConTom
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_title: Our campaign is about lifting up others on our way to victory
ad_creative_body: Our campaign is about lifting up others on our way to victory. Thanks to the whole Nevada For Tom team, that's exactly what we're doing. Let's get this done, Nevada!
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: Will you commit to vote or caucus for Tom in your state?
ad_creative_link_title: We need everyone to show up
ad_creative_body: This is shaping up to be the most important election of our lifetimes, and we need all hands on deck at the Nevada caucuses on February 22. If you can't be there, make sure you early vote at any early voting location in the county where you're registered to vote between February 15 and February 18.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: I'm making my stand
ad_creative_body: I know people can be critical of my decision to run for president. But I was taught that when you see evil in the world, you have to do something about it. The challenges facing our nation -- historic levels of economic inequality, skyrocketing health care costs, environmental destruction -- are the result of abject political cruelty. This is me making my stand.
label: Economic,Environment,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_title: I can beat Trump on the economy
ad_creative_body: As a true self-made businessman, I can beat Trump on his supposed strength: the economy. Yes, the economy is growing, but all the gains have gone to those at the top. As president, I'll use my decades of experience as a successful businessman to build an economy that works for everyone.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_title: The criminal justice system is broken
ad_creative_body: There's something wrong with a society that incarcerates more people per capita than any other country in the world. I sat down with formerly incarcerated individuals to better understand the challenges they face and share my plans for reforming the criminal justice system.
label: Economic,Safety

ad_creative_link_description: A pair of progressive groups gave Tom Steyer's plan to address the courts the top grade out of the field of Democratic presidential candidates and warned that the party's potential nominees need to make the issue more of a priority.
ad_creative_link_title: My court reform plan received the highest mark
ad_creative_body: My plan for court reform just received the top score from key progressive groups. Republicans have packed the court with right-wing ideologues who will shape policy for decades, threatening our democracy. I'll expand the Supreme Court to ensure it is representative of the American people.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: We asked Tom Steyer 20 questions on subjects that include debating President Trump, economic priorities and celebrity crushes.
ad_creative_link_title: 20 questions with the NYT
ad_creative_body: I sat down with the New York Times to answer 20 questions. We covered everything from addressing racism to achieving carbon neutrality. Take a look at what I had to say.
label: Environment,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: If you're ready for the government to prioritize education, join our campaign.
ad_creative_link_title: I'll raise high school graduation rates
ad_creative_body: Raising the high school graduation rate will generate billions for the economy and give millions of kids a chance at success. In my first term, I'll halve the dropout rate by ensuring kids meet reading benchmarks and providing a tutor to every student performing below grade level. If you're ready to give our young adults the support they deserve, sign on to our campaign.
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: If you're ready for the government to prioritize education, join our campaign.
ad_creative_link_title: I'll close the school readiness gap
ad_creative_body: Combating rising inequality starts with investing in early education. As president, I'll guarantee free, universal access to high quality pre-school and expand services for low-income pregnant women and families with young children. Join our campaign to give all our children an equal shot at success.
label: Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: If you're ready for the government to prioritize education, join our campaign.
ad_creative_link_title: We need to address the student mental health crisis
ad_creative_body: Our children and teens are in the midst of a mental health crisis. To tackle this growing epidemic, I'll double the number of mental health professionals on school campuses and implement evidence-based school mental health programs. Join our campaign to invest in our students' mental health.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Presidential candidate Tom Steyer (D) revealed his education plan designed to double federal funding for pre-K through 12th grade education.
ad_creative_link_title: Investing in education is the smart thing to do
ad_creative_body: As a society, the smartest investment we can make is in our people. That's why my education plan will double federal funding for preK-12 education. We'll guarantee universal access to preschool, close the school resource gap, and ensure teachers receive the compensation they deserve.
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: (RNS) — Known for his environmental advocacy, Tom Steyer, like other candidates, has made a point of referencing his faith often while on the campaign trail. He spoke with RNS to discuss his faith, how it intersects with his policy agenda, and the overlap between religion and politics in the Unite...
ad_creative_link_title: It's our responsibility to preserve our planet
ad_creative_body: My faith has informed my politics, particularly my views on climate change. We have a responsibility to protect vulnerable people and preserve the planet we've been given. That's what fighting climate change is all about.
label: Environment,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: If you're ready for the government to prioritize education, join our campaign.
ad_creative_link_title: Education reform starts with supporting educators
ad_creative_body: To strengthen our education system, we need to first invest in our teachers. We'll ensure teachers get paid the same as other skilled professionals and forgive student loans after 10 years of service. Join our campaign to give our educators the respect and support they deserve.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: If you're ready for the government to prioritize education, join our campaign.
ad_creative_link_title: The health of our democracy depends on civic education
ad_creative_body: Only 1/4 of Americans can name the three branches of government. My education plan will invest in civic education so American citizens are engaged, informed, and able to hold their leaders accountable. If you're with us, join our campaign today.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: During a CNN town hall in New Hampshire, Democratic presidential candidate Tom Steyer is asked about when he realized he needed to step away from his company, which invested in coal and oil, to focus on the climate crisis.
ad_creative_link_title: We can solve the climate crisis
ad_creative_body: Here's the good news about the climate crisis: we can solve it. This could be our greatest opportunity to rebuild our nation and unite the people around a common purpose.
label: Environment

ad_creative_link_description: Voters have realized that as a DC outsider and a true self-made businessman, Tom is the best candidate to beat Trump in 2020. Let’s keep the momentum going.
ad_creative_link_title: We're surging in SC
ad_creative_body: We've surged to 2nd in South Carolina! As a DC outsider, I'm not afraid to call for sweeping reforms to address racial inequality, economic injustice, and climate change -- and voters are getting excited about what we can do. Join them by signing on to our campaign today.
label: Economic,Environment,Governance,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: As an artist/activist, I'm forever indebted to the confidence instilled in me by my historically black university, Johnson C. Smith University. As a first-generation college graduate, it gave me a
ad_creative_link_title: We'll invest $125 billion in HBCUs
ad_creative_body: Jeremiah Chapman is a spoken word artist, proud HBCU graduate, and the social impact director for our campaign. He worked with us to develop our HBCU policy. We plan to invest $125 billion in HBCUs so they can continue educating and empowering students like Jeremiah.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: There's nothing more powerful than the unified voice of the American people.
ad_creative_link_title: Take the NV caucuses survey
ad_creative_body: The Nevada caucuses are right around the corner. Fill out our short survey to tell us who you'll be backing on February 22.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: There's nothing more powerful than the unified voice of the American people.
ad_creative_link_title: Who are you caucusing for?
ad_creative_body: Who are you supporting in the Nevada caucuses on February 22? Take a few seconds to let us know!
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: Billionaire Democrat gaining support in US state with large African-American population
ad_creative_link_title: We're committed to the African American community
ad_creative_body: Our campaign is investing in the African American community in South Carolina. We're doing what other candidates aren't: hiring black staffers, working with black businesses, and meeting the people where they are. When we say we're committed to lifting up our communities of color, we mean it.
label: Economic,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: To hear Steyer tell it, it’s simple why he would choose to spend the second to last weekend before the Iowa caucus in Nevada while all of his opponents are halfway across the country: He's a Westerner. But it's also strategic.
ad_creative_link_title: I've been on the ground in NV for years
ad_creative_body: I've been involved in grassroots movements in Nevada for years. My nonprofit NextGen America helped Democrats win key races in the Silver State, and in 2018, I was instrumental in passing a measure to raise Nevada's clean energy standards. When I say I'm committed to the people of Nevada, I mean it.
label: Environment,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Democratic Presidential candidate Tom Steyer was back in the Silver State, Saturday.
ad_creative_link_title: Trump has failed NV
ad_creative_body: Trump has failed Nevada. As president, I'll clean up the mess he created. We'll make the climate crisis our number one priority, invest more in education so our children can thrive, and end human rights abuses against immigrants.
label: Environment,Foreign policy,Immigration,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: COLUMBIA, S.C. (AP) — Democratic presidential candidate Tom Steyer is proposing a criminal justice reform plan that would reduce the costs of incarceration by redirecting funds to education,...
ad_creative_link_title: We must end racial bias in the criminal justice system
ad_creative_body: Racial bias permeates every aspect of the criminal justice system. My criminal justice plan will target institutional racism by mandating anti-bias training for police officers, ending cash bail, investing in programs for at-risk youth, and supporting formerly incarcerated individuals as they transition back to society.
label: Safety,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: The billionaire presidential candidate Tom Steyer reiterated his support Wednesday for reparations for African- Americans suffering from the legacy of slavery.
ad_creative_link_title: It’s time to talk about race
ad_creative_body: As a DC outsider, I’m not afraid to say it: you can’t talk about any major policy area without talking about race. It’s time to retell the story of the last 400 years. That’s why I’ll create a formal commission on reparations as president.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: Biden still has a wide lead in the polls, but the billionaire businessman has made an impression with voters.
ad_creative_link_title: I'm on the rise in SC
ad_creative_body: A recent poll put me 2nd in South Carolina, and it was no fluke. I'm meeting South Carolinians where they are. Our SC team is 90% African American, and the majority are organizing in the communities where they grew up. We're pushing power back to the people.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Biden still has a wide lead in the polls, but the billionaire businessman has made an impression with voters.
ad_creative_link_title: Our message is resonating in SC
ad_creative_body: I'm on the rise in South Carolina. When South Carolinians meet me, they see I'm fiercely committed to fighting for racial and economic justice. We're partnering with South Carolinians, employing South Carolinians, and listening to what South Carolinians have to say.
label: Economic,Social and Cultural

I know we can defeat this president and turn the page. But we’re up against some of the most well-funded politicians in Washington and need your help. Please chip in today and join our movement.

ad_creative_body:

Will you step up and make a donation today to help us win?
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Chip in to Help Us Defeat Donald Trump
ad_creative_body:
We're in the fight of our lives. We need to put together the majority that can decisively defeat Donald Trump. And to do that we need a politics that is defined not by who we reject, but how we bring everybody into the fold. 

Please chip in today if you agree that this is a time for addition and belonging, not rejection and exclusion.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Chip In Today
ad_creative_body:
In this election season, we have been told by some that we must either be for a revolution or for the status quo. But where does that leave the rest of us—the majority of us?

Our campaign offers a different choice. We believe that we can gather that majority together to build an American experience defined by belonging. If you share this belief, please chip in today and join our movement.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Chip In Today
ad_creative_body:
To defeat Donald Trump, the Democratic nominee needs to be able to bring everybody into the fold and unite the party. By building the broadest coalition and winning among first-time caucusgoers and voters in both Iowa and New Hampshire, we have proven that we are the campaign to do this.

If you share this belief in a politics of addition and belonging, please chip in and help us get our message out to every corner of the country in these critical weeks.
label: Foreign policy,Governance

ad_creative_body:
Latino families across the country are getting crushed by health care costs and Washington is doing nothing. I'm running for U.S. Senate to fight for affordable health care for everyone - that means lowering: 
❌ Premiums
❌ Deductibles
❌ Copays
❌ Prescription drug prices
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_body: We need quality, affordable health care for Latino families. Period.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_body:
When I was Governor, we built one of the most innovative health care exchanges in the country and got nearly 95% of Coloradans covered. 

I'm ready to fight to expand access to health care for the 21% of Latinos under the age of 65 without insurance.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_title: Read Pete's Plan
ad_creative_body: Women’s right to control their own bodies is under assault all over the country. As president, I will stand up to protect the rights of women to make their own health care decisions.
label: Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: Averigua más sobre Pete Buttigieg
ad_creative_body: Debemos asegurarnos de que la compasión anime nuestra política, que podamos sentir lo que está en juego para las personas que no comparten nuestra experiencia de vida.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_title: Sign up to Early Vote for Pete in Nevada
ad_creative_body: Did you know you can vote early in Nevada from February 15th to February 18th if you can't make it to the Caucuses on the 22nd? Sign up and we'll make sure you have all the information you need.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_title: What's the price tag on M4A?
ad_creative_body: Affordable health care must be a universal right, not a privilege. This is something that all my Democratic peers and I agree on. But how we get there is a different story. I’m calling on Senator Bernie Sanders to disclose the actual price tag of his Medicare for All plan. Will you join me?
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_title: Averigua más sobre Pete Buttigieg
ad_creative_body: Este es nuestro momento. Tenemos exactamente una sola oportunidad para derrotar a Donald Trump y al Trumpismo – y para eso tenemos que hacer algo distinto.  Únete a mi campaña y busquemos una nueva forma de hacer política.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_title: Vote for Bernie & return your mail-in ballot NOW
ad_creative_body: Voting for Bernie by mail? Mail in your ballot TODAY or drop it off in person before 8pm on Tuesday, March 3, at your county elections office a ballot drop box, or your polling location.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Voting for Bernie? Return your mail-in ballot before March 3
ad_creative_body:
If Bernie Sanders supporters make sure to cast their ballot for Bernie in California’s primary, we are going to win. So if you’re ready to elect Bernie, mail in your ballot right now OR return it at:
✅ Your polling place
✅ Your county elections office
✅ A county ballot drop box

Remember: your ballot MUST be received by 8pm on Tuesday, March 3, to be counted.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Vote for Bernie & return your mail-in ballot NOW
ad_creative_body: If you’re ready to help elect Bernie, then return your mail-in ballot right away. It only takes a few minutes, but it is so important, because we are counting on an unprecedented number of people coming out to win this race and transform this country.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Learn more about Pete Buttigieg
ad_creative_body: This is our chance to build a future defined by unity.

ad_creative_body:
"U.S. Rep. Steven Horsford, the only black member of Nevada’s congressional delegation, is endorsing Joe Biden for president on the eve of early voting in the state’s caucuses.

All of the Democratic candidates vying for your support want to put an end to Trump’s cruel attacks on health care and bring the peace of mind of health coverage to every American. But I am the only one running who has actually gotten big, bold health reform done.
 
Nevadans need a president who understands that the worst thing you could do for people struggling with a health crisis is destroy the Affordable Care Act. I believe the best way forward is to build on Obamacare with a Medicare-like public option for every single American who wants it.

Cory Booker has a lifetime of experience with Black voters — he’s been one since he was eighteen. 

He knows that our party’s nominee must work with people of color to deliver solutions and create justice and opportunity for everyone. He knows that the War on Drugs is a war on Black and Brown people and we need change now.

If you agree that our president should work with communities of color, not against them, donate whatever you can today. Help us keep up the momentum.

🚨We raised $6.6 million - more than any other quarter so far

🚨63% of the money we raised last quarter came from grassroots supporters online — like you
🚨96% of the people who gave for the first time, gave through an email, text message, or an online ad — just like this one

We’re not slowing down or losing pace — quite the opposite. Join this growing movement by giving whatever you can today.

This month, we are one year away from Election Day in 2020.

A lot will happen in the next year, but our priority must be this: we need to unite every member of our party in common purpose to fight for our values and build a national movement. 

Will you chip in what you can today to join me in that fight?

ad_creative_body:

Cory hasn’t yet qualified for the January debate stage. Chip in today to make sure he’s there.
label: Governance

Join them, and donate today to help keep up the momentum.
label: Governance

ad_creative_body: Cory Booker won the December debate — even though he wasn’t on stage. These caucus-goers know that he’s the candidate to restore justice and create equal opportunity for every American. Are you with them? Donate today.
label: Governance

ad_creative_body:
Cory Booker knows that the War on Drugs has been a war on Black and Brown people. That’s why he’s in favor of legalizing marijuana and why he’s spent his career fighting for, and delivering for, entire communities that have been left behind.

If you’re with him, donate today to help him keep up the momentum.

ad_creative_body:
In less than a year, we’ll be at the polls, ready to elect Democrats up and down the ballot.  

I know that when we come together in common purpose and fight for our shared values, we will do more than take back the White House. We will heal our country and undo the damage Trump has inflicted. 

I want you in this fight. If you’re with us, can we count on you to donate what you can today?
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Keep our campaign going strong
ad_creative_link_title: Chip in today
ad_creative_body:
We won’t take back the White House and undo the damage Trump has done alone, which is why we need a candidate who will bring America together. Cory Booker is that candidate.

Together, we will win and together, America, we will rise. 

Chip in whatever you can today to make sure our movement to take back our country continues to grow.

ad_creative_link_description: Together, we will rise.
ad_creative_link_title: Join this movement.
ad_creative_body: The call of this election is the call to unite in common cause and common purpose. As your president, that’s how I will move this country forward.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: Together, we will rise.
ad_creative_link_title: Join this movement.
ad_creative_body:
There are people who believe it’s naive to think that this election is first and foremost about our values and our ideals. To them I say, the only way we can win -- the only way we’ve ever won -- is to bring people together.

I’m running for president to unite Americans in common cause and common purpose to create justice and opportunity for everyone. Will you join me?
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Together, we will rise.
ad_creative_link_title: Join this movement.
ad_creative_body: It’s time to turn the page on the Trump presidency. After we defeat him in 2020, we’ll need a leader who can begin the healing process, who can undo the damage he’s caused, and who can unite our deeply divided country.
label: no topic

ad_creative_link_description: Together, we will rise.
ad_creative_link_title: Join this movement.
ad_creative_body:
This is a moment in America when we need a leader who can inspire us again. 

As your president, I will bring together uncommon coalitions in common purpose to move our country forward.

If you’re ready to see moral leadership from the White House, join my campaign for president.

ad_creative_link_description: The Tom Steyer staff invite you to a delicious private luncheon and Precinct Captain training catered by Las Vegas' very own Makers and Finders. Tom Steyer will be in there! This will be a fun and interactive training to prepare you for caucus day.
ad_creative_link_title: Hope to see you there!

label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Meet Tom Steyer in Pahrump this Wednesday!
ad_creative_link_title: Hope to see you there!
ad_creative_body: The best part of running for president is meeting Americans – whoever they are, wherever they are. Can you attend my meet and greet in Pahrump on Wednesday, February 19? I hope to see you there!
label: Governance

This is a spectacular moment to come together and celebrate....

When it comes to communities of color -- the backbone of our party -- Democratic candidates too often show up in church in the last few weeks of an election. At some point, folks get tired of that. After powering a Senate victory in Alabama and the 2018 midterm success across the country, women of color are asking for more. Where have you been and what are you going to do? And do you understand what the people want?

I’ve got experience of working with these communities. That means women, that’s people of color, that’s our LGTBQ community, that’s working people, that’s our labor unions. 

That’s how we win. And I intend to win. Chip in now to build a coalition that will take back the White House.

Where I come from, leaders don't eat until our troops are fed, and when it's time to jump out of an aircraft, we go first. When I came home after 24 years of service, I learned that 319,063 West Virginians are living at or below the poverty line while our so-called leaders are driving to work in BMWs. 

I'm ready to put my boots on the ground again, but I can't win this seat on my own. Will you donate now to help us flip this open seat?

ad_creative_body:
Too many children in West Virginia have fallen victim to addiction. 

This is why WV needs long term, comprehensive recovery. 

60 days in jail is not rehab. 
30 days detox is not rehab. 

Currently southern WV has 75 beds for recovery, and until we have politicians that aren't in the pocket of Big Pharma more families will continue to lose loved ones. 

#NotOneMore

ad_creative_link_description: 312 Laurel St, Columbia, SC 29201-2234, United States
ad_creative_link_title: Run With Mayor Wayne Columbia, South Carolina
ad_creative_body:
Meet 2020 Presidential Candidate & Miramar, Florida Mayor Wayne Messam at Riverfront Park and Historic Columbia Canal for a jog. Mayor Wayne continues his "Run With Mayor Wayne Tour in Columbia, South Carolina where voters can join Wayne and area runners for a run around the park followed by a meet and greet. Wear comfortable clothes and running shoes and your questions. 
Upon arrival, look for a 6'-5", dark and athletic looking Presidential Candidate to begin the run.

MEET WAYNE
I learned the values of hard work and pride of community from a young age. My parents immigrated to South Florida from Jamaica with just a 5th grade education, seeking greater opportunity for our family. My father labored for 16 years in the sugar cane fields of the Florida Glades after coming to the United States, and my mom would cook to feed the migrant workers. I was born in rural Pahokee, Florida and grew up in South Bay.

Thanks to the opportunity this country provided for my family, the support of my parents and mentors, and lots of time and effort in class and on the field, I earned a full football scholarship to Florida State University, where I started at wide receiver and was a member of the 1993 National Championship team.

After my NFL dreams were cut short, my wife Angela and I built one of the fastest-growing, minority-owned construction businesses in the country and our projects in the educational and non-profit space have garnered national recognition, including from the U.S. Green Building Council for building one of the greenest schools in the Southeast United States.

I then went into public service, first as a city commissioner, then rising to serve as a two-term mayor of Miramar—one of Florida’s most diverse cities.

Today, Miramar ranks as one of the fastest-growing city economies in the country. We actively foster innovation and development, from starting an aviation expo and tech camps to expose young people to the tools that can solve the problems of today and tomorrow.

I am proud of our record in Miramar as we’ve:

Fought to bring American jobs back from China.
Passed a living wage for city workers.
Recruited companies with high-paying jobs to hire Floridians.
Led the fight against the oil industry’s campaign to drill in Big Cypress National Preserve, adjacent to the Everglades and just a few miles from our city.
Joined mayors across the country to oppose climate denialism and pledge to support the goals of the Paris Agreement.
Taken on the Trump administration to protect immigrants, proposing our city as a safe zone for those who come to this country seeking a better life.
Sued the state of Florida to protect our residents from gun violence and overturn a law backed by the NRA.
Proposed and passed relief on water bills for federal workers who were impacted by the shutdown.
My college sweetheart, business partner, and better half Angela and I have been married for more than 20 years as we’ve built our lives in Miramar and raised our kids. Our three children, Wayne II and twin daughters Kayla and Kyla, attend college in South Florida.

Paid for by Wayne Messam for America

Donald Trump announced that he’s coming to Colorado to campaign for our opponent Cory Gardner, just days after Gardner stood with Senate Republicans to block firsthand witness testimony and cover-up for the president’s abuses of power.

This is the beginning of a new effort to tear down our campaign, and we’re expecting Trump to attack me personally and for those attacks to be amplified by Mitch McConnell’s secret money donor network.

We have to fight back today. Trump and McConnell’s attack machine is breaking fundraising records left and right, and the only way we can counter them is by collecting as many grassroots donations as possible. So, we’ve set an ambitious goal of raising $250,000 by tomorrow night, and we need you to make a contribution of any amount to help us get there:

Can I count on you to make an urgent donation of $10 or more to my campaign right now? I need your support to fight back against whatever Trump and McConnell have planned for our campaign in the coming weeks and months.

ad_creative_body:
Every kid in America should have the same access to a high-quality public education—no matter where they live, the color of their skin, or how much money their parents make. Elizabeth has a comprehensive plan for our public education system. Her plan invests hundreds of billions of dollars in our public schools, paid for by a small wealth tax on fortunes above $50 million. It also funds schools equitably, invests in school infrastructure, fights back against segregation and discrimination, protects the rights of English Language Learners and immigrant students, better supports teachers, and provides a warm, safe, and nurturing school climate for all of our kids. 

If you agree that we need to make big changes to improve public schools for our kids, sign up today. 

***

Todos los estudiantes estadounidenses deberían tener el mismo acceso a una educación pública de alta calidad—sin importar dónde vivan, el color de su piel o cuánto dinero ganan sus padres. Elizabeth tiene un plan comprensivo para mejorar nuestro sistema de educación pública. Su plan invierte cientos de miles de millones de dólares, pagado por un pequeño impuesto sobre las grandes fortunas de más de $50 millones. También financia las escuelas públicas de manera adecuada, invierte en la infraestructura de los planteles escolares, lucha contra la segregación y discriminación, protege los derechos de los estudiantes aprendices de inglés y los estudiantes inmigrantes, apoya de mejor manera a los educadores y provee un ambiente escolar alegre, seguro y acogedor para todos los estudiantes. 

Si estás de acuerdo que necesitamos hacer grandes cambios para mejorar nuestras escuelas públicas para nuestros niños, inscríbete hoy.
label: Economic,Environment,Immigration,Safety,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Inscríbete para utilizar nuestra calculadora y ver cuánto incrementarían tus beneficios.
ad_creative_link_title: Valuing The Work of Latinas | Valorando el trabajo de las latinas
ad_creative_body:
Our society and our economy demand so much of women — but they place a particular burden on Latinas and other women of color. More than 40% of Latina mothers are their families’ sole breadwinners, and Latinas on average make $0.53 for every $1 that white men make. 

Our economy should work just as hard for Latinas as Latinas work for our economy and their families. That’s why Elizabeth introduced a plan: a set of executive actions to implement on day one of the Warren administration to boost wages for women of color, open up new pathways to the leadership positions they deserve, and strengthen and target enforcement against systemic discrimination. If you agree with Elizabeth’s plan, sign up today.

***

Nuestra sociedad y economía exigen tanto de las mujeres, pero ponen una carga particularmente difícil sobre las latinas y mujeres de color. Más del 40% de las madres latinas son las proveedoras principales de sus hogares y en promedio, las latinas ganan solamente 53 centavos en comparación con el dólar que ganan los hombres blancos.

Nuestra economía debería trabajar tan arduamente por las latinas en el mercado laboral como ellas trabajan por impulsar nuestra economía y mantener a sus familias. Es por eso que Elizabeth tiene un plan que incluye una serie de acciones ejecutivas que implementará en el primer día de su administración para aumentar los salarios de todas las mujeres de color, abrir nuevos caminos a las posiciones de liderazgo que merecen y fortalecer acciones contra la discriminación sistémica. Inscríbete hoy si estás de acuerdo con el plan de Elizabeth.
label: Economic,Governance,Safety,Social and Cultural

For decades, students have worked hard and played by the rules. They took on loans on the promise that a college education would justify their debt and provide a ticket to the middle class. But our country’s experiment with debt-financed education went terribly wrong: instead of getting ahead, millions of student loan borrowers are barely treading water.

I’ve already proposed bold steps to cancel student loan debt, along with making public two- and four-year colleges and technical schools tuition-free, ban for-profit colleges from receiving federal aid, and help end racial disparities in college enrollment and resources. But the Department of Education already has broad legal authority to cancel student debt, and we can’t afford to wait for Congress to act. 

So I will start to use existing laws on day one of my presidency to implement my student loan debt cancellation plan that offers relief to 42 million Americans -- in addition to using all available tools to address racial disparities in higher education, crack down on for-profit institutions, and eliminate predatory lending. 

If you agree that we need to tackle the student debt crisis from all angles, sign on to my plan today.
label: Economic,Environment,Foreign policy,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

Trump grew up in a mansion in New York City. Elizabeth grew up in a middle class family in Oklahoma. 

He got millions from his dad’s real estate empire. Her dad ended up a janitor. 

He scammed students at his for-profit school. She got debt forgiven for students who were scammed.

Trump’s life taught him how to get rich on the backs of others. And he’s abused the presidency to do just that. Elizabeth Warren has spent her career fighting corruption for working people. And she will be a president who works for you.

“If a former Trump supporter can be energized by Elizabeth Warren, then Elizabeth Warren is doing something great for America.”

Mike caucused for Donald Trump in 2016, Antonio caucused for Bernie Sanders, and Bridget caucused for Hillary Clinton. 

But in 2020, they’re all caucusing for Elizabeth Warren, because they know Elizabeth can unite us and beat Donald Trump. 

Join them in fighting for a democracy that works for everyone. Click here to commit to caucus for Elizabeth.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_title: Trump is the man to beat — and Elizabeth is the woman who will do it.
ad_creative_body:

“Elizabeth Warren isn’t afraid to fight for the little guy. She’s helped so many people throughout her life. And her first priority is ending corruption, and that’s what this country needs.”

Join Stephen, and click here to commit to caucus for Elizabeth.

ad_creative_body:
Elizabeth Warren is fighting for working families because she comes from a working family. 

After her father had a heart attack and couldn’t work, they struggled and almost lost their family home.

That’s why she fought to hold Wall Street accountable for preying on working people and leading them into never-ending debt and bankruptcy. It’s why she torched CEOs who cheated students with fraudulent loans. And it’s why she calls Donald Trump out for his corruption and deceit. 
 
Elizabeth is a fighter who will beat Donald Trump. And when she wins, she’ll fight like hell to make this a country that works for everyone. 

Elizabeth Warren está luchando por las familias trabajadoras porque ella viene de una familia trabajadora. 

Luego de que su padre sufriera un infarto que lo dejó sin poder trabajar, su familia batalló para salir adelante.

Es por eso que ella luchó para responsabilizar a Wall Street por engañar a las personas trabajadoras, llevándolos a deudas interminables y la bancarrota. Es por eso que ella cuestionó a ejecutivos que engañaron a estudiantes. Y es por eso que ella critica a Donald Trump por su corrupción y fraude.

Elizabeth es una luchadora que vencerá a Donald Trump. Y cuando gane, luchará con todo para hacer que este país funcione para todos.
label: Economic

This is a critical time in our campaign, and we need your help now more than ever. Sign up for a volunteer shift today, and you’ll be entered to win a trip to meet Elizabeth at the next debate in New Hampshire! Flights and hotel are on us.

ad_creative_body:
I’m proposing a tax on the top 0.1% — the Jeff Bezoses and Mark Zuckerbergs of the world — that would generate trillions over the next ten years. Sounds good, right? It gets even better: I’ll use that money to reinvigorate the middle class by investing in our kids, from cradle to college. 

This plan will pay for:
- Universal child care for our kids, age 0 to 5,
- A great public K-12 education for all of our kids,
- Universal free technical, two-year, and four-year college,
- Student loan debt cancellation for 42 million Americans, and
- A minimum of $50 billion for HBCUs and Minority-Serving Institutions.

These issues are truly personal for me. I started out my career teaching kids with special needs in a public school. Later on I became a law professor and taught many bright minds at the collegiate level too. My dream job was to be a teacher; but I only achieved it because I was lucky to find affordable education options and to have free child care in the form of my Aunt Bee. Nowadays, most families aren’t so lucky. 

That’s why I’ve proposed the ultra-millionaire tax. The ultra-wealthy made their riches on the backs of American families. It’s time for them to pay it forward, and it’s time for us to tax the ultra-rich. Sign on to join our movement if you agree.
label: Economic,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth was just endorsed by the Des Moines Register. Commit to caucus for her today!
ad_creative_body:
Big news! The Des Moines Register just endorsed Elizabeth.
Here’s what they had to say: “Warren doesn’t measure the health of the economy by looking at the stock market or an unemployment rate that doesn’t count the longtime jobless or chronically underemployed. She measures it by how working families are doing. Many are not doing well, and Warren seeks major reforms to help them.”

Elizabeth Warren will be the best president money can’t buy. Click here to commit to caucus for Elizabeth on Monday, February 3rd.
label: Economic,Governance

Before February 3, we’re using every resource we have to reach undecided Iowans — because each one we reach is a chance to inspire one more person to caucus for Elizabeth.

It may be hard to believe, but I don’t drink coffee. The truth is, I get my energy from talking to people across the country about their big dreams and their hard-fought struggles, and from the power of the movement we’re building together. (And I’ll admit, I won’t say no to the occasional cup of tea.)
 
Now that 2020 has begun, this election is kicking into high gear. We’ve got to be laser-focused on making the investments we need in our organizing, advertising, and GOTV programs. I’m so proud of this team, but we still have a lot of work to do before caucuses are held and votes are cast. 

That’s why I’m asking you to sustain this movement — like a cup of coffee may help get you through the work day. Donate the cost of your usual $3 pick-me-up to keep us going today.

This is the most critical period of time in this primary, and Elizabeth needs your support now more than ever. Your donation will help fund our organizing efforts in these last few weeks before the Iowa caucuses and voting begins in New Hampshire, Nevada, South Carolina, and the rest of the country.

Don’t be left off the team — jump in and be a part of this grassroots movement by chipping in today.

Can a woman beat Donald Trump? Look at the men on stage at the most recent debate. Collectively, they have lost ten elections. The only people on that stage who have won every single election that they’ve been in are the women. 

The real danger that we face as Democrats is picking a candidate who can’t pull our party together — or someone who takes big parts of the democratic constituency for granted. We need a candidate who will excite all parts of our party and bring everyone in.

To join the fight for big structural change and be a part of our winning team, chip in $5 or whatever you’re able today.

New poll from the Des Moines Register:
- Bernie Sanders: 20%
- Elizabeth Warren: 17%
- Pete Buttigieg: 16%
- Joe Biden: 15%

The Des Moines Register just released a new poll that has Elizabeth in a close second in Iowa. In fact, all four top candidates are within the poll’s margin of error — meaning any one of them could win. This race is going to come down to which campaign has the most people make calls, knock on doors, and bring in the most grassroots donations in the next three weeks.

We’re just weeks from the Iowa caucuses and this poll shows what we already know: What we’re doing is working.

And we know what we need to keep doing in Iowa and everywhere — talk with caucus-goers and voters from the heart about Elizabeth’s plans for big, structural change.

We do that by running an unbeatable ground operation, and our job now is to make sure our organizers on the ground in Iowa have all the resources they need to get the most Iowans to the caucuses as possible.  

We have the ground game to win this race — but Elizabeth is not going to get there without your help. Rush a donation of $3 or whatever you can and help this grassroots movement expand our efforts in Iowa at this critical moment.
label: Foreign policy,Governance

My plan not only gets every American covered through Medicare for All — it saves time and money from dealing with insurance companies and puts those resources back into hospitals and patients.

In the past year, tens of thousands of health care workers have chipped in what they could to keep us in this fight for a democracy and an economy that works for everyone. Not special interests or drug company executives.

We need more hard working Americans like you to keep our grassroots movement going. Chip in now.
label: Economic,Foreign policy,Governance,Social Programs

I’m grateful down to my toes that Secretary Julián Castro is endorsing our campaign and joining our movement for big, structural change!

Julián has been a powerful voice for bold, progressive change. We both had the honor to serve in President Obama’s administration, and now we’re fighting side by side to ensure that families in our country today can have the same opportunity to achieve their dreams as ours did. 

It’s going to take all of us working together to get to the finish line. If you’re with Julián and me, sign up to join our team today.

In 2005, the banking industry, with its deep pockets and Congressional allies, successfully passed a bankruptcy bill that devastated families across the country who needed relief from debt collection.

That 2005 bill made the 2008 financial crisis significantly worse: experts found that the bill “caused about 800,000 additional mortgage defaults and 250,000 additional foreclosures.” 

Here’s the kicker: the banking industry spent more than $100 million to turn that bill into law because they knew it would be worth much more than that to their bottom lines. And they were right — by squeezing families harder, they managed to rake in giant profits. 

That’s why I’m announcing my plan to repeal the harmful provisions in the 2005 bankruptcy bill and overhaul consumer bankruptcy rules in this country. If you agree we need to overhaul our consumer bankruptcy system to give people a second chance, sign on to my plan today.
label: Economic

ad_creative_body:
I spent most of my career studying one simple question: why do American families go broke? 

I found that no one — not even the supposed “experts” — had actually dug into the data to figure out what drove families into bankruptcy. So I found two incredible partners and set out to gather the data about why families go broke. That was back when you had to collect information by hand, and courts charged a lot to make copies for you. To save money, I flew around to courthouses all over the country with my own photocopier — nicknamed R2D2 — strapped into the airplane seat next to me, copying thousands of bankruptcy filings to begin understanding why American families turned to bankruptcy. 

I’ll never forget sitting in a wood-paneled courtroom in San Antonio on one of my first trips, watching the families filing for bankruptcy move in and out of the courtroom to appear in front of the judge. They looked just like the family I grew up in — hanging on to the ragged edge of the middle class. Now they were standing in front of a judge, ready to give up nearly everything they owned just to get some relief from the bill collectors. 

Our research ended up showing that most of these families weren’t reckless or irresponsible — what many people thought at the time — they were just getting squeezed by an economy that forced them to take on more debt and more risk to cling to their place in America’s middle class. And that meant one bad break could send them tumbling over the edge. 

My plan aims to undo the harm of the 2005 banking industry-backed bill that made it harder for families to get the relief they need and overhaul consumer bankruptcy rules. As president, I will:
- Make it easier for people being crushed by debt to obtain relief through bankruptcy.
- Expand people’s rights to take care of themselves and their children while they are in the bankruptcy process.
- End the absurd rules that make it nearly impossible to discharge student loan debt in bankruptcy.
- Let more people protect their homes and cars in bankruptcy so they can start from a firm foundation when they start to pick up the pieces and rebuild their financial lives.
- Help address shameful racial and gender disparities that plague our bankruptcy system.
- Close loopholes that allow the wealthy and corporate creditors to abuse the bankruptcy system at the expense of everyone else. 

If you agree we need to overhaul our consumer bankruptcy system to give people a second chance, sign on to my plan today.
label: Economic,Governance,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

From bus blockades in Denver, Section 504 sit-ins in San Francisco, and the Deaf President Now student movement in D.C. to protests outside of Mitch McConnell's office and virtual marches, disability activists across the country have organized over decades to bring the nation’s attention to the injustices they face. Fighting a world that has excluded, exploited, and institutionalized them, they have put their lives on the line for a more just future and changed this country for the better for everyone.

As President, I will work in partnership with the disability community to combat ableism. I will fight alongside them for justice across all aspects of life and to fulfill the four goals of the ADA: equal opportunity, full participation, independent living, and economic self sufficiency. I’ll start by making clear that disability is a priority in my administration, creating a National Office of Disability Coordination to ensure that federal programs work together to support people with disabilities.

We must protect the rights and equality of people with disabilities. If you’re with me, sign on to my plan today.
label: Economic,Governance,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

“Democratic presidential candidate Elizabeth Warren suggests her plan to eliminate student loan debt may address population losses in rural Iowa.”

“Warren told the crowd student loan repayment plans aren’t adjusted by zip code.”

“‘Folks who’ve got to meet that nut every single month are a lot more likely to head out to the two coasts. I hear this from families all over Iowa,’ Warren said. ‘We cancel student loan debt for 43 million Americans, we make it a lot easier for people to decide to live their lives right here in small towns Iowa. I think that’s important.’”

Our country is deeply divided, but people across this country—Republicans, Independents, and Democrats—agree that our top priority has to be fighting corruption in Washington.

We’re dealing with a president who came to Washington claiming that he would “drain the swamp” of corruption. He broke that promise and has done everything he can to help the wealthy and well-connected.

I’m not doing big-dollar fundraisers in exclusive wine caves. I’m not selling my time to billionaires. I’m not selling ambassadorships to donors. My first priority as president will be to pass the biggest package of anti-corruption reforms since Watergate.

We’re going to shut the revolving door between Wall Street and Washington, end lobbying as we know it, and take power away from the rich and powerful and put it where it belongs—in the hands of the American people. Americans are ready to root out corruption and fight back—and I’ve got a plan for that.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: It’s long past time for bold, structural change to reform our criminal justice system.
ad_creative_link_title: Let’s fight for fair trials for every American.
ad_creative_body:
Prosecutors are also enormously powerful and often not subject to scrutiny or accountability. I will support a set of reforms that would rein in the most egregious prosecutorial abuses and make the system fairer, including reducing the use of coercive plea bargaining at the federal level and putting in place responsible standards for evidence gathering. And I’ll create an independent prosecutorial integrity unit to hold accountable prosecutors who abuse their power.

If you want to help fight for a fairer justice system, sign up now.
label: Safety

ad_creative_link_title: I'm not afraid to fight back.
ad_creative_body:
Our government is paralyzed. Why? Because the wealthy and giant corporations spend billions every year to get Washington to put their interests ahead of the public interest. We need to call this what it is—corruption, plain and simple. 

Corruption has put our planet at risk, broken our economy, and it is breaking our democracy.

I have the biggest anti-corruption plan since Watergate, to tackle the corruption that’s squeezing working people and undermining our democracy.

I know what’s broken in this country. Learn more about my plan to fix it.
label: Economic

We’ll be honest with you—Wall Street and Silicon Valley are excited about some of the other Democrats running for president. 

Other candidates are raising big bucks from fancy fundraisers with millionaires and billionaires. One candidate just spent an evening in a “wine cave” in Napa Valley adorned with chandeliers with more than a thousand Swarovski crystals.

I’m running to be the best president that money can’t buy. That means I’m not cozying up to the wealthy and well-connected the way some other candidates are. I’m not hosting any fundraisers where you can only meet me if you can write a check for $2,800. And I'm not taking any money from Washington lobbyists or PACs of any kind.

You'll always know that I'm fighting for you — not for any powerful special interest with deep pockets.

I'm grateful down to my toes for everyone who knocks on doors, make phone calls, texts their friends about our new plans, hosts debate watch parties, and chips in $3 at a time. For everyone who makes this campaign their own. For everyone who's in this fight all the way.

Our grassroots movement is up against a big test. On the FEC filing deadline on December 31st, we'll release a public report on how much we've raised in the past three months and how many people have chipped in to own a piece of our campaign.

We need those fundraising numbers to be as strong as possible, and we're behind where we want to be to hit our fundraising goals.

We can show the power of grassroots donors coming together as one movement. Will you chip in $5, $20 or whatever you can to help grow our grassroots movement?
label: Economic,Governance

Climate scientists published new research suggesting the planet is hurtling towards an ecological tipping point that would irreversibly damage the earth and threaten our livable climate — for good. This most recent study adds to the growing body of evidence that climate change is happening faster than scientists originally thought. And it further reinforces what we already know: we have roughly a decade left to avoid catastrophic impacts by ending our economic dependence on fossil fuels and substantially reducing global emissions. 

But while climate change presents an urgent threat, it also presents the greatest opportunity of our time: the chance to rebuild our economy with 100% clean energy, to address the racial and economic inequality embedded in our fossil fuel economy, and to create millions of good, union jobs in the process. 

America has a long and proud history of rising to the challenges that have faced this country — and defeating the climate crisis is no exception. A Warren administration will ensure that as we fight climate change, each and every American benefits from the opportunities created by the clean economy — creating 10.6 million new green jobs topower our transition to 100% clean energy. 

We will invest in these green jobs to:
- Expand job training
- Partner with unions to rebuild the middle class
- Move to 100% clean energy
- Transform the energy, transportation, water, and housing sectors to make room for these new jobs

If you’re with me on creating green jobs for the future of our country, sign on today.
label: Economic,Environment,Foreign policy,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_body:
Donald Trump has spent his career embracing shady deals. Trump has repeatedly partnered with shady actors on real estate deals that reek of money laundering, corruption, and fraud. More than one-fifth of all Trump’s U.S. condo sales since the 1980s have been all-cash transactions with shell companies — red flags that often indicate money laundering. At one of Trump’s towers in Florida, more than 60 percent of its units are owned by shell companies. And it doesn’t stop with real estate — over half of Trump’s more than 500 companies are registered in Delaware, taking advantage of state loopholes that exempt LLCs from publishing their financial information or disclosing their ownership structure.  

I’ve introduced the most ambitious set of domestic anti-corruption reforms since Watergate to clean up our government. But we must go further. Our domestic challenges are compounded by a global network that connects secretive shell companies, complicated trusts, middlemen and enablers that specialize in papering suspicious transactions, and states and countries that profit from a lack of transparency. To truly root out corruption, we must also tackle the flow of dark money around the world. If you’re with me, sign on today.
label: Economic,Foreign policy,Governance

ad_creative_body:
This campaign is powered entirely by folks like you — no super PACs, no corporate PACs, no high-dollar, closed-door fundraisers. 

We’re building a grassroots movement to put power in the hands of people. That means rooting out corruption in Washington, strengthening our democracy, and making sure the wealthy pay their fair share. We’re fighting for big, structural change in this country, and I can’t do it without your help. 

That’s why I’m asking for your help today. Donating now is more important than ever as we approach the last FEC deadline before votes are cast in the new year. 

Our daily donor goal in New York is 256. If everyone who sees this ad chips in just $5, we’d hit that goal in no time. Donate what you can today to help our grassroots campaign move forward.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: The next president has a moral obligation to use whatever executive authority she has to address the gun crisis.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Address America’s Gun Violence Epidemic and Save Thousands of Lives
ad_creative_body:
While the majority of Americans — including a majority of gun owners — support sensible gun control, even the most basic proposals are consistently blocked by far-right members of Congress who are bought and paid for by the gun industry, their NRA partners, and a supporting army of lobbyists and lawyers. 

In 2017, almost 40,000 people died from guns in the United States. My goal as president, and for our society, will be to reduce that number by 80%.
 
As president, I will immediately take executive action to rein in an out-of-control gun industry — and to hold both gun dealers and manufacturers accountable for the gun violence.
I will break the NRA’s stranglehold on Congress by passing sweeping anti-corruption legislation and eliminating the filibuster to free our nation from the small group of well-financed extremists who have already made it perfectly clear that they will never put the safety of the American people first.

I will send Congress comprehensive gun violence prevention legislation. I will sign it into law within my first 100 days. And we will revisit this comprehensive legislation every single year to continually reduce the number of gun deaths in America.

If you agree that it’s time to take action on guns and save lives, add your name.
label: Foreign policy,Governance,Military,Safety

ad_creative_link_description: The next president has a moral obligation to use whatever executive authority she has to address the gun crisis.
ad_creative_link_title: We need to do everything possible to keep guns out of the hands of those at highest risk of violence.
ad_creative_body:
Under a Warren administration, we’ll prohibit anyone convicted of a hate crime from owning a gun. Too often, guns are used in acts of mass violence intended to provoke fear in minority communities. More than 10,000 hate crimes involve a gun every year. Any individual convicted of a hate crime should be permanently prohibited from owning a gun, full stop. 

Domestic violence and gun violence are deeply connected. In an average month, more than 50 women are shot and killed by an intimate partner. I’ll close the boyfriend loophole, but Congress should make that permanent, and expand the law to include individuals with restraining orders or who have been convicted of stalking.

The shooting in El Paso also reminds us that we need to call out white nationalism for what it is: domestic terrorism. Instead of a president who winks and nods as white nationalism gets stronger in this country, we need a president who will use all the tools available to prevent it. It is completely incompatible with our American values, it is a threat to American safety and security, and a Warren Justice Department will prosecute it to the fullest extent of the law.

If you’re with me, sign up now.
label: Foreign policy,Safety,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Has A Plan To End Offshore Drilling
ad_creative_body:
The BP Deepwater Horizon oil spill — the worst oil spill in our nation's history — caused more than $17 billion in damage to natural resources and cost eleven lives. Years later, coastal economies and ecosystems along the Gulf Coast have still not recovered. On day one of my presidency I will sign a sweeping executive order with bold actions to defeat the climate crisis, including ending all new fossil fuel leases offshore and on public lands. 

But new offshore fossil fuel leases are only part of the problem — we must also phase out existing offshore drilling, which is putting the health and economies of coastal communities at risk. 

If you’re with me on ending offshore drilling, sign on today.
label: Economic,Environment,Governance

ad_creative_body:
The BP Deepwater Horizon oil spill — the worst oil spill in our nation's history — caused more than $17 billion in damage to natural resources and cost eleven lives. Years later, coastal economies and ecosystems along the Gulf Coast have still not recovered. On day one of my presidency I will sign a sweeping executive order with bold actions to defeat the climate crisis, including ending all new fossil fuel leases offshore and on public lands. 

But new offshore fossil fuel leases are only part of the problem -- we must also phase out existing offshore drilling, which is putting the health and economies of coastal communities at risk. A Warren administration will start by reinstating the Obama Administration’s Outer Continental Shelf Oil and Gas Leasing Program that protected more than hundreds of millions of acres in the Atlantic Ocean and Arctic. We’ll also reinstate the well safety rules that the Obama administration put in place after the BP oil spill, because the fossil fuel workers who risk their lives to power our economy deserve safe working conditions. And we’ll roll back the Trump administration’s decision to reduce the shallow-water royalty rate for existing offshore drilling leases. In fact, we’ll go further: we’ll reassess the royalty rate to more accurately account for the social cost of carbon. Over the last two decades, some of the world’s largest oil companies, including Chevron, Exxon, and Shell, have skirted about $18 billion in federal royalties from offshore drilling. That ends in a Warren Administration. 

I will direct federal ocean and coastal management agencies to begin planning to phase out all offshore drilling. Instead, we will focus on transitioning the offshore drilling supply chain and associated industry to offshore wind. I am committed to leaving no worker behind as we transition to 100% clean energy, and the men and women who have tirelessly worked in the offshore drilling industry are no exception. A Warren administration will provide job training and guaranteed wage and benefit parity for workers who choose to transition into new industries. And for those Americans who choose not to find new employment and wish to retire with dignity, we’ll ensure full financial security, including promised pensions and early retirement benefits. 

If you’re with me on ending offshore drilling, sign on today.
label: Economic,Environment,Governance,Safety,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

The Sixth Amendment provides every American accused of a crime with the right to an attorney — but too many defendants cannot afford one, and too often, public defenders are under-resourced, overworked, and overwhelmed. If we expect fair trials, we need to balance resources on both sides of each case, everywhere. I’ll fund federal public defenders and expand targeted grant funding for public defenders at the state level, to ensure that they have the tools to effectively defend their clients. We should ensure that our public defenders are paid a fair salary for their work, and that their caseloads allow for the comprehensive defense of their clients. And I’ll provide funding for language and cultural competency training, including on gender identity and treatment of individuals with disabilities, so that public defenders are best able to serve their clients.

If you want to help fight for a fairer justice system, sign up now.
label: Safety,Social and Cultural

The United States makes up 5% of the world’s population, but nearly 20% of the world’s prison population. We have the highest rate of incarceration in the world, with over 2 million people in prison and jail. Our system is the result of the dozens of choices we’ve made — choices that together stack the deck against the poor and the disadvantaged. To make matters worse, the evidence is clear that there are structural race problems in this system. Today in America, there is one criminal justice system for the rich and powerful, and another one for everybody else. It’s long past time for us to reform our system. 

Under my new plan, we will reduce incarceration and improve justice in our country by changing what we choose to criminalize, reforming police behavior and improving police-community relations, and making structural changes to our justice system. When people are incarcerated, we will provide opportunities for treatment, education and rehabilitation, and we’ll continue those supports for returning citizens as they rejoin our communities. Most importantly, we’ll rethink the way we approach public safety — emphasizing preventative approaches over law enforcement and incarceration. That’s the way we’ll create real law and order and real justice in our country. 

If you’re ready to fight for equal justice under the law, sign up now.
label: Safety,Social Programs

The vast majority of police officers sign up so they can protect their communities. But many people of color disproportionately experience trauma at the hands of law enforcement, sometimes with life-altering consequences. On average, three people are shot and killed by the police every day, a disproportionate number of them young and Black. Others are arrested and entered into a system that unduly penalizes even minor infractions. It’s time to fundamentally change how police work is done in America: funding what works; replacing failed policies with effective, evidence-based practices that do not violate individual rights; and reframing our approach to public safety to prioritize prevention over punishment. 

We will improve justice in our country by reforming police behavior and improving police-community relations. If you’re with me, sign up now.

As some of the other Democratic campaigns have begun to stall, handfuls of their wealthy supporters are gearing up to start Super PACs for candidates who can’t mobilize enough grassroots support.

That means Wall Street, billionaires, and giant corporations can dump unlimited sums of money into the Democratic primary to back whatever candidate they think will help them most. 

They’ve seen the strength of our grassroots movement, and they know that if we win, we’ll take political and economic power out of their hands and put it where it belongs — in the hands of the people.

Those powerful special interests are ready to jump at the chance to spend ridiculous amounts of money in the primary — and against everything we’re fighting for.

That’s where you come in. We’re building a grassroots movement powered by folks like you, not billionaires or CEOs. If you’re ready to join us, chip in whatever you can today.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Donate to Warren for President. Your grassroots support keeps us in this fight.
