ad_creative_body:
Elizabeth’s Ultra-Millionaire Tax—a two-cent tax on fortunes above $50 million—would pay for universal child care, canceling student loan debt for 95% of those who have it, a minimum $50 billion investment in HBCUs, and more. 

But lately, some of the wealthy few that would be affected by the tax have started going on national television, literally shedding tears, writing op-eds, and trying to stop our movement in its tracks. And now Michael Bloomberg—one of the first billionaires to attack Elizabeth’s plan for a wealth tax—is taking steps to enter the Democratic primary. 

The wealthy and well-connected are scared that, under a Warren presidency, they would no longer have a government that caters to their every need. So they’re doing everything they can to try to stop Elizabeth and our grassroots movement from winning. 

Let’s defeat the billionaires and make our government and our economy work for working people. Chip in now.
label: Economic,Governance,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: By working together – by listening to and learning from each other – we’ll make sure we’re ready to fight and win together.
ad_creative_link_title: The Best President Money Can’t Buy
ad_creative_body:
Kamala Harris and Kirsten Gillibrand — two women senators who, together, won more than 11.5 million votes in their last elections — have been forced out of this race, while billionaires Tom Steyer and Michael Bloomberg have been allowed to buy their way in.

Our democracy should not be for sale, and yet, billionaires have been able to use their money to try to buy this election outright.

Elizabeth is running to be the best president that money can't buy. She doesn't sell her time to the wealthy, doesn't hold fancy fundraisers with special access for big donors, and isn't beholden to corporate interests or their lobbyists. She's in this fight for working people.

We're going to root out corruption in Washington right at the source — and level the playing field for working people in this country. Sign on to join our grassroots movement.
label: Economic,Governance,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_body:
“In a Medium post Friday morning, 29 women state legislators endorse Sen. Elizabeth Warren for president, calling her the best candidate to ‘fight for our families and get our government back on track.’”

“The House members write that Warren’s plans and approach to governing are aimed at ‘putting an end to the corruption that has led to many New Hampshire families being left behind and making sure our government works for everyone.’”
label: Governance,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: HANOVER — Democratic presidential hopeful Elizabeth Warren laid out a range of plans aimed at rooting out corruption and improving life for the middle class during a campaign stop on Thursday in Dartmouth College’s Bema amphitheater.Standing in front...
ad_creative_link_title: Warren Pitches Plans For Equality During Dartmouth College Stop
ad_creative_body:
“Standing in front of an American flag, under a canopy of colorful fall leaves, the Massachusetts senator gave about 1,100 people there a brief biography before describing her plans to upend the systems she said are enriching corporations at the expense of working Americans.”

“Warren’s plans to root out corruption include ending ‘lobbying as we know it,’ closing the ‘revolving door’ between Washington and Wall Street, and making the Supreme Court ‘follow basic rules of ethics.’”
label: Economic

ad_creative_link_description: AS A FORMER five-term state senator and Democratic candidate for governor, I have had many opportunities to see and hear firsthand what Granite Staters need from their government. The people
ad_creative_link_title: NH Voices: Molly Kelly — I'm All In For Senator Warren And Here Is Why
ad_creative_body:
“I am honored to be endorsing Elizabeth during the campaign’s Women with Warren month. As women organize for Elizabeth across the state, I’m reminded that New Hampshire women — like women across the country — are underpaid for the same work men do. Elizabeth has long fought for equal justice and opportunity for everyone, across gender, race, age, sexual identity, immigration status and more.”

“She is in this fight to build an America that works for everyone. Her comprehensive policy plans are meant to ensure that the government works for all of us — not just those at the top. Elizabeth understands that economic injustice is the core of a system that is failing families in New Hampshire and around the county and she is ready to change that!”
label: Economic,Immigration,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Massachusetts Senator, Elizabeth Warren, visited Carson City where she talked to hundreds of voters about what she hopes to accomplish if elected president.
ad_creative_link_title: Senator Warren Talks to Hundreds of Voters in the Capital City
ad_creative_body:
“Matthew Brown, a concerned father, said to see the room filled with empowering energy makes it clear for him on who should take over in our nation's capital.”

"’I think it would be very beneficial for us right now, especially universal pre-k and universal health care which is very important to us especially with two young daughters, I would love to have a female president,’ Brown said.”
label: Environment,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: She won a two-minute standing ovation from thousands of party activists Saturday, came out on top in a poll released Sunday, and is seen as the one to beat.
ad_creative_link_title: The Rise, and Rise, and Rise Of Elizabeth Warren in New Hampshire
ad_creative_body:
“The battle for the hearts of New Hampshire progressives is on. And now, for the first time, Senator Elizabeth Warren is winning it.”
“She won a two-minute standing ovation from thousands of party activists Saturday, came out on top in a poll released Sunday, and is seen as the one to beat, according to interviews with approximately two dozen New Hampshire Democrats this week.”
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Sen. Elizabeth Warren On Black Women Maternal Mortality: 'Hold Health Systems Accountable For Protecting Black Moms'
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Boost Wages for Women of Color on Day One
ad_creative_body: Our society and our economy demand so much of women — but they place a particular burden on Black, Latina, Native American, and other women of color. That’s why I have a new plan: a set of executive actions I will take on day one of the Warren administration to boost wages for women of color and open up new pathways to the leadership positions they deserve. It’s time for the government to value the work of women of color — and boost our economy in the process.
label: Economic,Governance,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: My plan to remove barriers to affordable housing for Black families
ad_creative_body:
Homeownership is out of reach for too many families — especially Black families. Decades of outright discrimination by the federal government denied Black families the same kinds of homeownership subsidies available to white families. Then government regulators ignored warning signs as predatory financial institutions targeted minority communities with subprime mortgages that sucked billions of dollars in wealth out of those communities.

The black homeownership rate today is nearly the same as it was when housing discrimination was legal. And we’re not going to solve our housing crisis by nibbling at the edges. We need to tackle it head on — with big, comprehensive solutions that match the size of the problems we have. That’s what my housing plan for America does.
label: Economic,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Justice must be at the center of our response to climate change. And we need big, bottom-up change - focused on, and led by, the communities who have been in this fight since the beginning.
ad_creative_link_title: We need to hold corporations accountable for their role in the climate crisis
ad_creative_body:
Financial institutions and the insurance industry underwrite and fund dirty fossil fuel investments around the world, and they could play a key role in stopping the climate crisis. Instead, the big banks have actually increased their fossil fuel investments since the Paris Climate Agreement was signed. 

My Climate Risk Disclosure Act would require banks and other companies to price their exposure to climate risk into their valuations, raising public awareness of just how dependent our economy is on fossil fuels. And let me be clear: in a Warren Administration, they will no longer be allowed to shift that burden to the rest of us. 

Click here to learn more about my plan to hold the big banks accountable for their role in the climate crisis.
label: Economic,Environment,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Environmental justice has increasingly gained attention in the presidential race
ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Warren Unveils an Environmental Justice Platform
ad_creative_body:
“The plan includes a range of specific policy prescriptions, from a promise to pursue criminal penalties for polluters to a spike in funding for programs that guarantee clean drinking water. Considered holistically, the plan would represent a sharp departure from the Trump-era during which experts say such concerns have been sidelined.

“‘Our crisis of environmental injustice is the result of decades of discrimination and environmental racism compounding in communities that have been overlooked for too long,’ she said in a statement accompanying the plan. ‘Justice cannot be a secondary concern.’”
label: Environment,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Previously, Warren had said she would not hold high-dollar fundraisers in the primary but could adjust later on to compete with Trump.
ad_creative_link_title: Warren swears off high-dollar fundraisers in potential general election
ad_creative_body:
“Warren’s promise at the outset of her campaign to not hold traditional closed-door fundraisers with the wealthy drew skepticism from many party strategists. But her campaign has defied the doubters to become a fundraising juggernaut. She raised $24.6 million this past quarter, trailing only Sanders among the Democratic primary contenders and significantly outpacing the candidates who held traditional fundraisers.

‘Look, for me, this is pretty straightforward,’ Warren told CBS News. ‘Either you think democracy works and electing a president is all about going behind closed doors with bazillionaires and corporate executives and lobbyists and scooping up as much money as possible... or you think it’s about a grass-roots, let’s build this from the ground up.’”
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Warren’s bold plan to crack down on corruption in Washington, explained.
ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Warren’s first priority as president: ending government corruption

ad_creative_link_description: Warren's plan fully finances the program without imposing any new taxes on middle-class families, writes Mark Zandi, chief economist of Moody's Analytics.
ad_creative_link_title: Economist: Warren is right. Her Medicare for All plan won't raise taxes on the middle class
ad_creative_body: “It's no secret that I'm not a fan of Medicare for All. That's why I'm impressed that Senator Elizabeth Warren's campaign reached out to me to independently review her proposed financing plan for the program. Her numbers add up and her plan fully finances the program without imposing any new taxes on middle-class families.”
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Elizabeth Warren spent Labor Day on the campaign trail in New Hampshire, drawing a crowd of 800 to a backyard in Hampton Falls. Granite State voters are starting to narrow down their choices in the presidential...
ad_creative_link_title: “I Know How to Win”: Elizabeth Warren Campaigns in New Hampshire on Labor Day
ad_creative_body:
“It’s a concern Rhodes took straight to Warren during the Q and A: ‘When I talk to friends and family and people all over the country, they say, ‘we love Elizabeth Warren, we love her policies, but can she really beat Donald Trump?’’

“‘How about we start with, I know how to fight and I know how to win,’ Warren responded to Rhodes.

“‘I think what’s going to carry us as Democrats is not playing it safe. I think you’ve got to give people a reason to show up and vote and that’s what I’m doing.’”
label: Safety

ad_creative_link_description: If winning the Democratic nomination requires wooing the party's progressive wing and harnessing the power of activist women, then Senator Elizabeth Warren has a plan...
ad_creative_link_title: One Woman, and Millions of People to Back Her Up
ad_creative_body:
“If winning the Democratic nomination requires wooing the party’s progressive wing and harnessing the power of activist women, then Senator Elizabeth Warren has a plan for that.

“At a rally in New York City’s Washington Square Park on Monday evening, just hours after she beat Senator Bernie Sanders for the coveted endorsement of the Working Families Party, Warren laid out a far-reaching anti-corruption plan that rooted her campaign in a long history of women reformers.

“But the speech also served as a road map for her path to the nomination, positioning Warren as the only candidate in the race who can knit together the women voters and progressive activists who propelled the Democrats to midterm victories in 2018.”
label: Governance,Military,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren on Tuesday unveiled plan for “getting big money out of politics,” which includes expanded disclosure and a ban on federal candidates taking corporate political action committee money.
ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Warren unveils plan to ‘get big money out of politics’
ad_creative_body: “State Rep. Francesca Diggs, D-Rumney, said, ‘Getting money out of politics so that our government works for all families is one of my top concerns. Elizabeth Warren’s campaign finance reform plan puts the interests of the people first, clearly showing the issue as a top priority and one of many reasons she has my support.’”
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Ms. Warren got the most enthusiastic response of the 19 candidates who appeared Saturday. Bernie Sanders, Pete Buttigieg and Cory Booker also attracted particularly energetic support.
ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Warren Stands Out at New Hampshire Democratic Party Convention
ad_creative_body:
“No one was embraced at the New Hampshire Democratic Party’s state convention Saturday quite like Elizabeth Warren.

“The Massachusetts senator took the stage to a standing ovation that lasted around two minutes, and the thunderous applause that frequently interrupted her speech was amplified by the inflatable noisemakers that had been distributed to the crowd. ‘Win with Warren!’ attendees yelled.

“‘There is a lot at stake, and people are scared,’ she said. ‘But we can’t choose a candidate we don’t believe in because we’re scared.’

“‘I am not afraid,’ Ms. Warren said as she called for a ‘grass-roots movement’ to create structural change. ‘And for Democrats to win, you can’t be afraid either.’”
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Elizabeth is calling for universal free public college and cancelling student loan debt for 42 million Americans.
ad_creative_link_title: I’m calling for something truly transformational: Universal free public college and cancellation of student loan debt
ad_creative_body:
Higher education opened a million doors for me. It’s how the daughter of a janitor got to become a teacher, a law school professor, a U.S. Senator, and eventually, a candidate for President of the United States.

Today, it’s virtually impossible for a young person to find that kind of opportunity. As states have invested less per-student at community colleges and public four-year colleges, the schools themselves have raised tuition and fees to make up the gap. And rather than stepping in to hold states accountable, or to pick up more of the tab and keep costs reasonable, the federal government went with a third option: pushing families that can’t afford to pay the outrageous costs of higher education towards taking out loans.

That’s why I’m calling for something truly transformational — the cancellation of up to $50,000 in student loan debt for 42 million Americans.

Once we’ve cleared out the debt that’s holding down an entire generation of Americans, we must ensure that we never have another student debt crisis again. We can do that by recognizing that a public college education is like a public K-12 education — a basic public good that should be available to everyone with free tuition and zero debt at graduation.
label: Economic,Governance,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Less than two weeks after releasing a sweeping student debt cancellation plan, Massachusetts Sen. Elizabeth Warren is promoting a student debt forgiveness calculator designed to show voters exactly how much they would benefit from her plan.…
ad_creative_link_title: Warren's Student Debt Calculator Shows How Her Plan Could Help You
ad_creative_body:
"’Anybody in here have student loan debt?’ Warren asked the crowd. ‘Anybody in here know someone with student loan debt? Okay, I think we got almost everybody.’

“She then asked people in the audience to take out their phones and plug their student debt amounts into the calculator, which can be found directly on her 2020 presidential campaign website.

“The calculator poses a short series of questions — about what type of schooling an individual took out loans for, how much student debt they accumulated, and how much their total income was the previous year. The calculator then uses that information to determine exactly how much of that individual's student debt would be canceled under Warren's plan.

“According to CNN, Warren's plan would eliminate up to $50,000 in student debt for anyone living in a household that earns less than $100,000 per year. People from households that make between $100,000 and $250,000 annually would have student debt canceled on a sliding scale proportional to their income, Business Insider reported, while those from households making $250,000 or more would not qualify for any student debt cancellation.”
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_body: On the debate stage, I made it clear: I’m tired of freeloading billionaires. My wealth tax asks for just a few cents from those billionaires, and it could fund universal pre-k, free college, and so much more. If you’re sick of the freeloading too, chip in and join our campaign.
label: Economic,Governance,Social Programs

ad_creative_body:
We need to ensure that everyone in this country has the opportunity to succeed. Here's what we could do with my two-cent #WealthTax: ✅ Universal Child Care and pre-k
✅ $800 billion dollars in our public schools
✅ $50 billion in #HBCUs
✅ Cancel student loan debt

#DemDebate
label: Economic,Governance,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: The senator from Massachusetts was met with the biggest crowd of the Des Moines Register Political Soapbox, with numbers easily in the thousands.
ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Warren, Met With The Largest Soapbox Crowd So Far, Touts Her 2-Cent Ultra-Millionaire Tax
ad_creative_body:
"‘[The] plan, which would impose a 2% tax on fortunes over $50 million, would fund universal child care and pre-kindergarten, provide tuition-free college, invest $50 billion into historically black colleges, and cancel student loan debt for an estimated 42 million people,’ she said on the Des Moines Register Political Soapbox at the Iowa State Fair on Saturday.

“‘We could do all that and still have a couple of hundred billion dollars left over. That should tell you about what's broken in America,’ Warren said. ‘Every time we see a budget, it’s really just a statement of our values. Is it more important to leave the two cents for the bazillionaires or use that two cents to invest in all of our kids?

"‘Well, I’m here because I think we ought to be investing in all of our kids.’"
label: Economic,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: “I just feel like Warren is more of the planner. And Bernie, while I love him for this, he’s definitely more of the idealist."
ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth Warren Is Winning Over Left-Wing Hearts In Iowa

"In Iowa alone, Warren has attended 36 events, spoken to more than 7,000 Iowans and taken almost 5,000 selfies over eight trips. She also employs more than 50 paid staff members in the state, which has garnered the attention of top local Democrats.

“‘I’ve done 90-plus town halls, I’ve taken literally thousands of questions. I’ve been to 20 states and Puerto Rico. And yeah, we’re coming up on our 30,000th selfie,’ Warren told the audience. ‘That’s how you build a grassroots movement.’

ad_creative_link_description: The first 2020 presidential candidate to campaign in Aiken made a sweeping appeal to South Carolina and Georgia voters Saturday by way of policy and platform discussions, some more locally
ad_creative_link_title: Democrat Elizabeth Warren Discusses Purpose, Policies At USC Aiken Rally
ad_creative_body:
“U.S. Sen. Elizabeth Warren, a Massachusetts Democrat, spent the evening at USC Aiken, speaking at length to hundreds of people in a gym and, before that, to an overflow crowd gathered outside on a nearby lawn. The event was attended by a total 925 people, according to her campaign.

“‘This is our moment in American history. It comes to us...to get organized, to build a grassroots movement, to persist and to build the country of our best values,’ Warren said, wrapping up her stump speech. While addressing the outdoor crowd, the senator said she was ready to turn the two-state region, a Republican safe haven, blue."
label: Governance,Safety

ad_creative_link_description: Add your name if you agree we need to fight back against white nationalist violence.
ad_creative_link_title: Fighting Back Against White Nationalist Violence
ad_creative_body:
Violent white nationalist attacks take place at different times, in different places across our country, but they share much in common. They were intended to create fear. They were motivated by hate and bias. And they are incompatible with our values and have no place in American life. 

The FBI logged more than 7,000 hate crimes last year, and the government’s own surveys suggest there are hundreds of thousands more that go unreported or uncategorized. 

In a Warren administration, we will use every tool we have to defeat domestic right-wing terrorism. Here’s what we’ll do: 
- We’ll prioritize the investigation and prosecution of white nationalist violence using the resources of the Departments of Justice and Homeland Security.
- We’ll tackle gun violence by expanding background checks, keeping guns out of the hands of those who may be violent, and preventing perpetrators of hate crimes from owning firearms. 
- We’ll invest in early prevention of extremist violence, teaching tolerance, and addressing incitement of violence on the Internet. 
- We’ll reform our police forces to protect targeted communities by tackling racially discriminatory policing, separating law enforcement from immigration enforcement, and better holding officers accountable when they violate a person’s constitutional rights. 

To take on hate, we all have to stand up against it — together. That’s why I’m in this fight, and I hope you’ll join me. Sign on today.
label: Foreign policy,Governance,Immigration,Safety,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_body:
Insurance companies, big pharma, and Republicans will fight any plan to improve health care. Making it all the way to Medicare for All won’t be easy, but I’ll fight my heart out to get this done for one simple reason. I spent a lifetime learning from working families who go broke. A huge reason for that is health care costs. 

Families shouldn’t go bankrupt because of health care costs. When I’m president, I’m going to do everything in my power to make sure that never happens to another person again. 

Here’s my plan — and it starts the day I take office: 
- In my first 100 days I’ll give everyone 50 and older the option to enroll in the existing Medicare program and let every person in America join a Medicare for All option for little or no cost.
- I’ll lower the cost of lifesaving drugs like insulin.
- I’ll crack down on Washington corruption to stop insurance and drug companies from blocking real change.

By the end of my third year as president, we’ll vote to transition everyone to Medicare for All. At this point, millions of Americans will likely have already experienced the full benefits of Medicare for All. They’ll be able to compare the new system against the corrupt and wasteful system that exists today, and the choice will be clearer than ever: Medicare for All is cheaper and provides better care. 

If you’re with us in this fight for Medicare for All, sign on today.
label: Economic,Safety,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Add your name if you agree we need to keep our promises to service members, veterans, and military families.
ad_creative_link_title: Keeping Our Promises To Service Members, Veterans, & Military Families
ad_creative_body:
All three of my brothers served in the military, so I know the responsibility we have to our service members, military families, and veterans. As Commander-in-Chief, I will lead our Armed Forces with awareness of the unique challenges service members and military families face, and the difficulties veterans encounter as they navigate the VA during their transition to civilian life. We need to exercise care in how we deploy our forces abroad, and we need to care for our veterans after they take off the uniform. I will prioritize our most important strategic asset – our people – as we reform Pentagon spending and address our most pressing national security crises. The way I see it, this is not complicated. It’s about a government that keeps its promises to those who served — it’s about our values. 

We can honor our veterans by ending these endless wars, reining in our bloated defense budget and reducing the influence of defense contractors at the Pentagon, and bringing our troops home responsibly — and then providing our veterans with the benefits they’ve earned. 

That’s why I’ve put together a comprehensive plan to keep our promises to service members, veterans, and military families. Sign up today if you’re with me on this.
label: Economic,Foreign policy,Governance,Military,Safety

Insurance and drug companies will spend millions in political contributions and disinformation campaigns against Medicare for All in order to keep billions in profits flowing in. We have to fight back against it. 

The truth is this: my Medicare for All plan covers everyone, saves the middle class a whopping $11 trillion, and is paid for largely by holding corporations and the wealthiest 1% accountable. The middle class won’t pay a penny more in taxes.

You don’t get what you don’t fight for, and I will fight to make Medicare for All a reality for all Americans. Sign up today if you’re with me.
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_title: My Plan To Pay For Medicare For All
ad_creative_body:
A lot of people have been curious about how I’ll pay for Medicare for All as president. I’ve got a plan for that. I’m proud that it’s the first health care plan by anyone in this presidential primary that lays out the full cost and how we can pay for it. Spoiler alert: it doesn’t raise middle-class taxes by one penny and saves American families $11 trillion on health care costs over the next ten years.

Here’s how it works:
- Taxes for middle class families will not go up — instead, my plan gives Americans an $11 trillion tax break.
- Costs will be covered by making the wealthiest 1% and big corporations pay their fair share. 

If you’re with me on this, sign up today.
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_title: It’s time for Congress to step up and begin impeachment proceedings.
ad_creative_body:
After the Mueller report, Congress had a duty to begin impeachment. By failing to act, Congress is complicit in Trump’s latest attempt to solicit foreign interference to aid him in US elections. Do your constitutional duty and impeach the president.

A president is sitting in the Oval Office, right now, who continues to commit crimes. He continues because he knows his Justice Department won't act and believes Congress won’t either. He thinks he’s above the law. If we do nothing, he’ll be right.

Mitch McConnell is also complicit. The Senate must vote on the bill, already passed by the House, to help states and localities protect themselves from the foreign attacks on our elections that the President has previously welcomed.

In 1974, Democrats and Republicans united in support of impeachment not out of mutual contempt for Nixon but mutual respect for the rule of law. Congress refused to be complicit in future law-breaking by Nixon or other presidents. It’s time for this Congress to step up and act. If you’re with me, sign up now.
label: Foreign policy,Governance,Safety

Today, climate change poses both an existential threat and a scientific challenge. We already see its effects — record floods, devastating wildfires, 100-year storms that happen every year — costing lives and billions of dollars in damage.
 
Here’s my plan to help tackle climate change head-on: Invest $2 trillion over the next ten years in American green research, manufacturing, and exporting — linking American innovation directly to American jobs, and helping achieve the ambitious domestic and international targets of the Green New Deal.

The science is clear: even if we reduce America’s emissions so that they are net-zero by 2030, we will still fall far short of the reduction in global emissions needed to avert a climate crisis. We need widespread domestic and international adoption of clean, renewable, and emission-free energy technology to meet the goals of the Green New Deal. That’s why I’m proposing a Green Marshall Plan — a commitment to use all the tools in our diplomatic and economic arsenal to encourage other countries to purchase and deploy American-made clean energy technology. This includes a new federal office dedicated to selling American-made clean, renewable, and emission-free energy technology abroad and a $100 billion commitment to assisting countries to purchase and deploy this technology. Sign up now if you agree that it’s time for a Green Marshall Plan.
label: Economic,Environment,Foreign policy,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: We need to fight to protect reproductive health care.
ad_creative_body:
Access to quality reproductive health services, including safe and legal abortion, is essential to a woman’s health and economic security. But systemic barriers have made it especially difficult for Black women to access the reproductive care they need.

This is a dark moment. People are scared and angry. And they are right to be. But the next president can begin to fix this and undo some of the damage done by the Trump Administration’s efforts to undermine women's health care. My plan lays out the steps to fight back.
label: Economic,Governance,Safety,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: My Plan for a High-Quality Public School Education for Every Kid in America
ad_creative_body:
I believe in America’s public schools, and I believe that every kid in America should have the same access to a high-quality public education — no matter what zip code they live in, the color of their skin, or how much money their parents make. 

Betsy DeVos has been a disaster as Secretary of Education, but funding for public K-12 education has been both inadequate and inequitable for too long. We’re failing to treat public school teachers, paraprofessionals, and school staff like the professionals they are. We need to pay them well, listen to them, and give them the support that they need.

I've got a plan to invest in public schools and ensure every kid in America has the same access to a high-quality public education. My plan will:

 • Fund schools adequately and equitably so that all students have access to a great public education.
 • Renew the fight against segregation and discrimination in our schools.
 • Provide a warm, safe, and nurturing school climate for all our kids.
 • Treat teachers and staff like the professionals they are. 
 • Stop the privatization and corruption of our public education system. 

And it would all be paid for by the Ultra-Millionaire Tax, a two cent tax on fortunes above $50 million.

Our students, public school educators, and parents deserve a president that will fight for them — and that’s the kind of president I’ll be. Add your name to support my plan for public education.
label: Economic,Environment,Safety,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

That means we’ll be able to quadruple Title I funding — an additional $450 billion over the next 10 years — to help every child get a high-quality public education. And we’ll invest an additional $200 billion in special education, at least an additional $50 billion in school infrastructure, and an additional $100 billion in “Excellence Grants” to give schools the chance to invest in programs and resources that they believe are most important to their students.

Add your name now to support my plan to invest billions of dollars into our public schools — all paid for by a two cent tax on ultra-millionaires.

ad_creative_link_description: Say you agree it's time to give our schools the support they need.
ad_creative_link_title: We will renew the fight against segregation and discrimination in our public schools
ad_creative_body:
Integrated schools improve educational outcomes for students of all races. And integrated schools are demanded by our Constitution. 

That’s why I’m committed to strengthening Title VI of the Civil Rights Act of 1964 — which prohibits discrimination on the basis of race in any program or activity that receives federal funding — and reviving robust enforcement of its terms.

My plan uses federal education funding to encourage states to further integrate their schools, and my administration will strictly enforce the right of students with disabilities to a free and appropriate public education and will protect the rights of LGBTQ+ students, English Language Learners, and immigrant students and their families.

Add your name now to fight against segregation and discrimination in our public schools.
label: Immigration,Safety,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

This movement is only possible when we all work together. Chip in to help us keep going.

The Supreme Court’s ruling blocking the citizenship question on the 2020 Census is a welcome relief — but the Court has left open the possibility that the Trump administration could still add a citizenship question to preemptively rig the results of the 2020 Census.

Right-wing extremists Steve Bannon and Kris Kobach pushed the Trump administration to add the question to suppress the count of immigrants, and Commerce Secretary Wilbur Ross lied about these contacts. Since then, the Trump administration has made every effort to conceal evidence about the racist and partisan decision to add the citizenship question to the 2020 Census. 

Make no mistake: The Trump administration pushed to add the question to scare Latinx Americans and suppress the count in immigrant communities so that these communities would be deprived of representation, funding, and necessary services. We cannot allow these intimidation tactics to succeed in silencing our voices — and that’s why we must fight back.

If the Trump administration somehow manages to get a citizenship question back on the Census, I would cancel that rigged Census and replace it with a fair and accurate one. And I’ll make this promise right now: A Warren administration would never include a citizenship question on the Census. 
If you’re with me, sign up now to fight back.
label: Foreign policy,Governance,Immigration,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: We need immigration reform that provides cost-effective security at our borders, addresses the root causes of migration, and provides a path to status and citizenship so that our neighbors don’t have to live in fear. Add your name if you agree.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Decriminalize Migration
ad_creative_body:
President Trump has weaponized deportation in ways that are costly, ineffective, and designed to maximize pain. It’s time to end this cruelty — and refocus on true threats to public safety and national security instead. As president, I will decriminalize migration and refocus enforcement on serious criminal activity.

Entering the country without authorization has always been a violation of civil immigration law, but thanks to a former segregationist Senator, it’s also a criminal violation. Since the early 2000s, this additional criminal provision has been used to build and sustain a massive immigration detention complex. 

In 2016, over half of all federal criminal prosecutions were for immigration violations — more than prosecutions for terrorism, organized crime, hate crimes, or financial fraud. This obsessive focus ties up federal prosecutors and overwhelms federal courts. It’s costly and unnecessary. And under Trump, it has become increasingly abusive. 
As president, I will immediately issue guidance to end criminal prosecutions for simple administrative immigration violations. If you’re with me, sign up today.
label: Economic,Foreign policy,Governance,Immigration,Safety

ad_creative_link_description: We need immigration reform that provides cost-effective security at our borders, addresses the root causes of migration, and provides a path to status and citizenship so that our neighbors don’t have to live in fear. Add your name if you agree.
ad_creative_link_title: As president, I will welcome 175,000 refugees per year by the end of my first term and affirm asylum protections for all who need it.
ad_creative_body:
Our laws and our values compel us to help those fleeing violence and oppression, but Trump’s racism has contributed to a climate of fear for those seeking refuge in our country. At a time when 70 million are displaced around the world, President Trump has abused his authority to lower the refugee cap for the United States, admitting just over 22,000 refugees in total last year. 

As president, I’ll welcome 125,000 refugees in my first year, and ramp up to at least 175,000 refugees per year by the end of my first term. We should welcome those fleeing violence, not imprison them in cages. So I will reverse Trump’s efforts to stack the deck against asylum applicants. I’ll ensure that asylum seekers can safely present themselves at ports of entry, and expand asylum protections for those fleeing domestic or gang violence and for gender identity and sexual orientation-based claims.

If you’re with me, sign up now.
label: Environment,Immigration,Social and Cultural

When I was growing up, before Roe v. Wade, people still got abortions. Some were lucky. Others weren’t. They all went through hell. The overwhelming majority of Americans have no desire to return to the world before Roe v. Wade. And so the time to act is now. 

I’ve got a plan to create federal, statutory rights that would invalidate state bans and protect the right to have an abortion nationwide. Add your name if you’re with me and ready to fight.
label: Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to clean up the corruption in our elections.
ad_creative_link_title: Let’s Ban Lobbyists from Donating, Bundling, and Fundraising for Candidates
ad_creative_body: When individuals who are paid to influence politicians also funnel money into the campaigns of those same politicians, that sounds like legalized bribery. My anti-corruption plan will end the corrupting influence of lobbyists throughout our government, including banning lobbyists from donating, bundling, and fundraising for candidates. It’s time to put power in the hands of the people where it belongs — sign up now if you agree.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to clean up the corruption in our elections.
ad_creative_link_title: It’s time to bring dark money into the light
ad_creative_body:
Citizens United cleared the way for massive super PACs and dark money organizations that funnel hundreds of millions of dollars into our politics on behalf of largely unknown donors. Every organization that makes an election-related expenditure should be required to promptly disclose their large donors. And super PACs and other dark money groups must provide enough information about the sources of their money so the American people can trace it back to the ultimate individuals and entities that are funding them — not just the shell organizations used to conceal those sources.

If you’re ready to put an end to dark money in politics, sign up now.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to clean up the corruption in our elections.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Publicly Fund Elections
ad_creative_body:
Right now, our system of funding elections allows individuals and PACs to donate huge sums of money to candidates and parties. We need to empower ordinary people through a small-dollar public financing system that gives candidates an incentive to spend more time courting working people, rather than just big donors. 

My plan will include a public financing program that would give a 6-1 match for small dollar contributions, less than $200. The program will be funded by penalties coming from corporate malfeasance and major tax crimes. Our democracy shouldn’t be bought and paid for by the wealthy and powerful. It belongs to all of us.

Sign up now to fight for publicly funded elections.
label: Economic,Governance

For decades, the FDA has banned gay and bisexual men from donating blood. This ban is outdated, discriminatory, and reduces the already limited blood supply. I helped lead the fight against this discriminatory ban and pushed the FDA to change its policies. While this change was an improvement, it does not go far enough. As president, I would lift this ban completely and make sure that any restrictions around blood donations are grounded in science and based on individual risk factors. 

If you’re ready to end the discriminatory blood donation ban for gay and bisexual men, sign up now.
label: Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to fight shoulder to shoulder for LGBTQ+ equality.
ad_creative_link_title: Religious liberty should not be used to shield bigotry
ad_creative_body:
We must prevent the weaponization of religion to discriminate against or harm LGBTQ+ people. The freedom of worship is a core American value. But the Trump White House has weaponized the language of religion by giving federal agencies, government contractors, and grantees a license to discriminate against LGBTQ+ people, as long as they claim they discriminated for a religious reason. Religious liberty should not be used to shield bigotry. As president, I will fight to pass the Do No Harm Act to guarantee that religious freedom can’t be used to harm LGBTQ+ people.

Sign up now if you’re with me.
label: Social and Cultural

Sign up now to join our fight to ban conversion therapy.

ad_creative_body:
Today, federal law still does not expressly prohibit firing a transgender person because of their gender identity, evicting a bisexual person because their same-sex partner moves in, or deliberately misgendering a non-binary student in the classroom. As president, I will fight to pass the Equality Act to explicitly guarantee that no LGBTQ+ person in America is discriminated against for who they are or who they love. 

There should be absolutely no question that LGBTQ+ people have equal rights under the law. That’s why I’m an original co-sponsor of the Equality Act, which would amend existing civil rights laws to explicitly ban discrimination on the basis of sexual orientation and gender identity in employment, housing, health care, education, public accommodations, credit, jury selection, and all federally-funded services. And if Senate Republicans put small-minded partisanship ahead of protecting these rights, I will end the filibuster so that we have a path to getting critical legislation like the Equality Act passed. 

Sign up now to join our fight to pass the Equality Act.
label: Governance,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to fight shoulder to shoulder for LGBTQ+ equality.
ad_creative_link_title: Every LGBTQ+ student deserves an equal opportunity to thrive
ad_creative_body:
Lesbian, gay, and bisexual youth are almost five times as likely to have attempted suicide as their straight peers. Ten percent of transgender people aged 18-25 reported having attempted suicide in the last year. As president, I’ll fight to make sure every LGBTQ+ young person is treated with dignity, fairness, and love at home and in school.

This starts by banning discrimination against sexual orientation and gender identity in our adoption agencies and child welfare system. We must also institute a nationwide ban on conversion therapy. And I will make it easier to change identification documents to reflect a person’s gender identity.

We must make schools safe environments for LGBTQ+ students. In 2017, more than half of LGBTQ+ students reported feeling unsafe at school because of their sexual orientation, and over 70% of LGBTQ+ students reported being verbally harassed or bullied. As a consequence, more than a third of LGBTQ+ students missed school during the previous month because they felt unsafe or uncomfortable. 

As president, I’ll fight to make sure every young LGBTQ+ person has an equal opportunity to thrive. If you’re with me, sign up now.
label: Safety,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_body:
The Supreme Court just heard three cases that threaten to roll back LGBTQ+ rights, allowing employers to fire workers because of their sexual orientation or gender identity. Now that President Trump has appointed two new Justices, Brett Kavanaugh and Neil Gorsuch, the Supreme Court could set LGBTQ+ rights back by years.  

No matter what happens at the Supreme Court, we need a president who will lift up the voices of every LGBTQ+ person, stand up to discrimination, and fight back. And as president, I will fight shoulder to shoulder with them – because no one should ever be unsafe, unheard, or disempowered because of who they are or who they love. 

If you’re ready to fight for LGBTQ+ equality with me, sign up now.
label: Economic,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to fight shoulder to shoulder for LGBTQ+ equality.
ad_creative_link_title: We need to take action to end the HIV/AIDS crisis
ad_creative_body:
We have made incredible strides and medical advancements toward ending the HIV/AIDS epidemic, but HIV/AIDS remains a public health crisis with 1.1 million people continuing to live with HIV in the U.S. today. A majority of these people are LGBTQ+, are from communities of color, and are contending with multiple barriers that prevent them from getting the care they need. We must demand more for them and for their futures. 

I will fight to increase funding for federal HIV/AIDS programs and research like the Ryan White Program, including the Minority HIV/AIDS Initiative, and HIV/AIDS treatment and cure research at the National Institutes of Health. 

We must also decriminalize HIV transmission and publicly manufacture PrEP, making the drug available to more people.

Sign up now to join our fight to end the HIV/AIDS crisis.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Justice cannot be a secondary concern — it must be at the center of our environmental response.
ad_creative_link_title: As president, I will fight for your job, your family, and your community like I would my own
ad_creative_body:
Climate change is a crisis — but it also represents a once-in-a-generation opportunity to create millions of good-paying American jobs in clean and renewable energy, infrastructure, and manufacturing. 

For too long, there has been a tension between transitioning to a green economy and creating good, union jobs. But we can do both. I’ve got a plan to create good new middle class jobs through investments in a clean economy coupled with the strongest possible protections for workers. 

If you’re ready to tackle the climate crisis and create millions of good, union jobs, sign up now.
label: Economic,Environment

ad_creative_link_description: Justice cannot be a secondary concern — it must be at the center of our environmental response.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Fight for Communities Hit First and Worst by Climate Change
ad_creative_body:
Climate change threatens all of us, and we must address it head-on. It’s time for a Green New Deal — and by ending oil and gas subsidies and reversing Trump’s tax cuts for the wealthiest individuals and giant corporations, we can make a down payment on the justice we need. 

The Green New Deal will deploy trillions of dollars to transform the way we source and use energy. In doing so, the government must prioritize resources to support communities hit first and worst by climate change, and correct historic injustices. My friend Governor Jay Inslee rightly challenged us to fund the most vulnerable communities first, and he’s right. I’ll direct one-third of my proposed climate investment into communities that are on the front lines of the climate crisis — a commitment that would funnel at least $1 trillion into these areas over the next decade. 

If you’re ready to fight for justice in our response to the climate crisis, sign up now.
label: Economic,Environment,Foreign policy

ad_creative_link_description: Justice cannot be a secondary concern — it must be at the center of our environmental response.
ad_creative_link_title: It’s Time for Medicare For All
ad_creative_body: People in underserved communities disproportionately suffer from certain cancers and other pollution-related illnesses. To make matters worse, they are less likely to have access to quality health care. Under Medicare for All, everyone will have high quality health care at a lower cost, allowing disadvantaged communities to get lifesaving services. If you’re ready to fight for Medicare for All, sign up now.
label: Social Programs

ad_creative_link_description: Justice cannot be a secondary concern — it must be at the center of our environmental response.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Fight for Justice as We Fight the Climate Crisis
ad_creative_body:
We have a crisis of environmental injustice, and it’s the result of ignoring decades of discrimination and environmental racism in underserved communities. For far too long, our government put corporate profits ahead of people. That’s wrong, and it must change. 

Justice must be at the center of our response to climate change. The Green New Deal commits us to a “just transition” for all communities and all workers. We must prioritize communities that have experienced historic disinvestment, across their range of needs: affordable housing, better infrastructure, good schools, access to health care, and good jobs. And we must fight to rebuild our unions and create real progress and justice for all workers as we transition to a clean energy economy.

We need strong communities that are prepared and properly resourced to withstand the impacts of climate change. We need big, structural change — focused on, and led by, members of these communities. If you’re ready to fight for environmental justice and a Green New Deal, sign up now.
label: Economic,Environment,Governance,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_description: We need big, structural change to root out corruption in Washington
ad_creative_link_title: We will ban members of Congress and senior government officials from owning or trading individual stocks.
ad_creative_body:
Under current law, members of Congress can trade stocks and then use their powerful positions to increase the value of those stocks and pad their own pockets. The solution is simple — as president, I will ban members of Congress and senior government officials from owning or trading individual stocks.

Sign up now if you’re ready to start cleaning up conflicts of interest in Washington.
label: Economic

ad_creative_link_description: We need big, structural change to root out corruption in Washington
ad_creative_link_title: We need to hold the federal judiciary to the highest ethical standards.
ad_creative_body:
Giant corporations and powerful interests haven’t limited their influence-peddling to Congress and the White House. They’ve also turned their attention to the courts. 

Today, every federal judge is bound by a Code of Conduct – except Supreme Court justices. It’s a recipe for corruption. We can fix it by applying the Code of Conduct for United States Judges to Supreme Court justices.  

As President, I will require judges to disclose key information so the American people can verify that their conduct is above ethical reproach. We will also close the loophole that allows federal judges to escape investigations for misconduct by stepping down from their post. 

Sexual assault and perjury complaints against Brett Kavanaugh were dismissed when he was confirmed to the Supreme Court – that’s ridiculous, and I’ve got a plan to fix it. Under my plan, investigations will remain open until their findings are made public and any penalties for misconduct are issued. 

Sign up now if you’re ready to hold our courts accountable to the American people.
label: Economic,Governance,Safety

ad_creative_link_title: Elizabeth is fighting for the middle class
ad_creative_body:
Show the American people your plans, and they’ll know what your values are. 

Elizabeth’s Ultra-Millionaire Tax would pay for
- Universal child care for every child from birth to school age 
- Student debt cancellation for 95% of people who have it 
- Tuition-free public college and technical school
- A minimum $50 billion fund for HBCUs

We can do a lot by asking ultra-millionaires and billionaires for just two cents. If you’re with Elizabeth, join your fellow Nevadans and add your name.
label: Economic,Social Programs,Social and Cultural

ad_creative_link_title: Health care costs will go down for middle class families
ad_creative_body:
Medicare for All is how we ensure that every Granite Stater is covered. 

Costs will go up for the wealthy and for big corporations — but they won’t go up for middle-class families. I will not sign a bill into law that would raise the costs for middle class families. 

If you’re with me on this, add your name today.
label: Economic,Social Programs

ad_creative_link_title: I know what’s broken, I know how to fix it, and I’ll fight to get it done
ad_creative_body:
We have an America that’s working better and better for a thinner and thinner slice at the top and leaving everyone else behind. 

This is our moment in history to provide real solutions to the country’s biggest problems. I know what’s broken, I know how to fix it, and, together with our grassroots movement, I’ll fight to get it done. Join other Granite Staters and add your name to be a part of it.
label: Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to clean up the corruption in our elections.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Get Big Money Out of Politics and Return Power to the People
ad_creative_body:
Every election, lobbyists and billionaires try to buy off politicians. Candidates and elected officials often spend hours and hours a day doing “call time” or jetting across the country to meet with big donors and corporate CEOs, instead of focusing on policy and working for their constituents. It’s corruption — and thanks to the Supreme Court, it’s perfectly legal. Enough is enough. It’s time to get big money out of politics.

When I’m president, I’ll implement a comprehensive plan to permanently eliminate big money from our politics and return power to the people. 

Sign up now if you agree that it’s time to end the corruption of our democracy.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to clean up the corruption in our elections.
ad_creative_link_title: We need modern campaign finance laws that address online political advertising
ad_creative_body:
The system of money for influence is helped, at every stage, by secrecy. In the lead up to the 2016 election, Russian nationals and Kremlin-connected businesses spent money on internet ads to influence American public opinion. Under current law, many of these ads were completely legal. My plan would modernize campaign finance law for the digital age by including internet ads in rules regulating election advertising, requiring large platforms to keep a “political file” with information about ad buys, just like TV and radio broadcasters do, and requiring large platforms to make reasonable efforts to prevent illegal ad buys by foreign nationals.

If you are ready to regulate political ads on the internet — like this one — sign up now.
label: Economic,Governance

ad_creative_link_description: Say you’re ready to clean up the corruption in our elections.
ad_creative_link_title: My Plan to Get Big Money Out of Politics and Return Power to the People
ad_creative_body:
Every election, lobbyists and billionaires try to buy off politicians. Candidates and elected officials often spend hours and hours a day doing “call time” with big donors, instead of focusing on policy and working for their constituents. They jet across the country, going from one closed-door fundraiser to another, hearing about the woes and challenges of being a billionaire or corporate CEO. And they court lobbyists and billionaires who can open the doors to thousands of dollars in PAC contributions or millions in super PAC spending. 

Let’s call this what it is: corruption. And thanks to the Supreme Court, it’s perfectly legal. The Court has declared that money is speech and corporations are people, and it has struck down many efforts to get big money out of politics. Since Citizens United in 2010, outside groups have more than tripled their spending on candidates and elections. Enough is enough. It’s time to get big money out of politics.

When I’m president, I’ll implement a comprehensive plan to permanently eliminate big money from our politics and return power to the people. 

My plan has three parts: 
 • End the corrupt system of money for influence,
 • Expand disclosure of fundraising and spending, and 
 • Put power back in the hands of the people.

To truly end the corruption of our democracy, we must pass a constitutional amendment to overturn the Supreme Court’s decisions in Citizens United and Buckley v. Valeo. A constitutional amendment will allow Congress to regulate election spending, establish public financing as the sole way to finance elections, and bring an end to the era of big money in politics.

Sign up now if you agree it’s time to get big money out of politics and return power to the people.
label: Economic,Governance
